obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (44245)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44245&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Transfer of Property Act, 1882.`
  line
  line `Commencements.-- It shall come into force on the first day of July, 1882.`
  line
  line `Extent.-- ^1[It extends ^2 in the first instance to the whole of India. except ^3[the`
  line `territories which, immediately before the 1st November, 1956, were comprised in Part B`
  line `States or in the States of], Bombay, Punjab and Delhi.]`
  line
  line `^4[But this Act or any part thereof may by ^5notification in the Official Gazette be`
  line `extended to the whole or any part of ^6[the said territories] by the State Government`
  line concerned.
  line
  line `^7[And any State Government may, ^8*** from time to time, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, exempt, either retrospectively or prospectively, any part of the territories`
  line `administered by such State Government from all or any of the following provisions,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `Sections 54, paragraphs 2 and 3, 59, 107 and 123.`
  line
  line `^9[Notwithstanding anything in the foregoing part of this section, sections 54, paragraphs 2`
  line `and 3, 59, 107 and 123 shall not extend or be extended to any district or tract of country for the`
  line `time being excluded from the operation of the Indian Registration Act, ^10[1908 (16 of 1908)],`
  line `under the power conferred by the first section of that Act or otherwise.]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for the third paragraph.`
  line
  line `2. The application of this Act was barred in the Naga Hills District, including the Mokokchung Sub -division, the`
  line `Dibrugarh Frontier Tract, the North Cachar Hills, the Garo Hills, the Khasi and Jantia Hills and the Mikir hills`
  line `Tract, by notification under s. 2 of the Assant Frontier Tracts Regulation, 1880 (2 of 1880).`
  line
  line `Partially extended to Berar by Act 4 of 1941. Extended to Manipur by Act 68 of 1956; to Dadra and Nagar Haveli`
  line `by Reg. 6 of 1963, s. 2 and Sch. I; to Goa, Daman and Diu by Reg. 11 of 1963, s. 3 and Sch.; to Lakshadweep by`
  line `Reg. 8 of 1965, s. 3 and Sch., to Pondicherry by Act 26 of 1968, s. 3 and Sch.`
  line
  line `It has been amended to Bombay by Bombay Act 14 of 1939, S7 of 1959, in U.P. by U.P. Act 24 of 1954, 14 of 1970 and 57`
  line `of 1976.`
  line
  line `Extended to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for "Part B States".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for the original paragraph.`
  line
  line `5. The Act has been extended to`
  line
  line `The Presidency of Bombay (except Scheduled Districts) w.e.f. 1-1-1893; to Mehwassi Estate by Born. Reg. 1`
  line `of 1949; and to former princely area w.e.f. 1-4-1951; now applicable to whole of Maharashtra;`
  line
  line `Gujarat (Saurashtra area) by Saurashtra Ordinance 25 of 1949, and to Kutch area w.e.f. 1-1-1950.`
  line
  line `Madhya Pradesh:`
  line
  line `Mysore, w.e.f. 1-4-1951;`
  line
  line `Rajasthan, w.e.f. 1-7-1952;`
  line
  line `the former State of Travancore-Cochin, w.e.f. 1-5-1952, now applicable to whole of Kerala.`
  line
  line `The provisions o( sections 54, 107 and 123 were extended to--`
  line
  line `Delhi, w.e.f. 30-5-1939. Section 129 was extended to certain areas of Delhi w.e.f. 16-11-1940 and to`
  line `the remaining areas w.e.f. 1-12-1962. the remaining provisions were also extended to the Union`
  line `territory of Delhi w.e.f. 1-12-1962;`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh, w.e.f. 7-12-1970:`
  line
  line `Punjab, w.e.f. 1-4-1955 and to former princely area w.e.f. 15-5-1957. (Section 59 was enforced in`
  line `Haryana area, w.e.f. 5-8-1967).`
  line
  line `The Act has been declared in force in the Pargana of Manpur by the Manpur Law Regulation, 1926 (2 of 1926),`
  line `in Panth Piploda by the Panth Piploda Laws Regulation, 1929 (1 of 1929) and in the State of Sikkim on`
  line `1.9.1984 vide Notification No. S.O. 643(E), dated 24-8-1984, Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Pt. II, sec.`
  line `3(0.`
  line
  line `The Act has been repealed as to Government Grants by the Government Grants Act, 1895 (15 of 1895).`
  line `The Act has been repealed or modified to the extent necessary to give effect to the provisions of Madras Act 3`
  line `of 1922, in the City of Madras see s. 13 of Madras Act 3 of 1922.`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for "the said States".`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 3 of 1885, s. 1, for the original paragraph.`
  line
  line `8. The words "with the previous sanction of the Governor General in Council" omitted by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and the`
  line Schedule.
  line
  line `9. Added by Act 3 of 1885, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-7-1882).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 2, for 1877.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (44100)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Repeal of Acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44100&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In the territories to which this Act extends for the time being the e nactments specified in`
  line `the Schedule hereto annexed shall be repealed to the extent therein mentioned. But nothing`
  line `herein contained shall he deemed to affect--`
  line
  line `(a) the provisions of any enactment not hereby expressly repealed;`
  line
  line `(b) any terms or incidents of any contract or constitution of property which are consistent`
  line `with the provisions of this Act, and arc allowed by the law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(c) any right or liability arising out of a legal relation constituted before this Act comes into force,`
  line `or any relief in respect of any such right or liability; or`
  line
  line `(d) save as provided by section 57 and Chapter IV of this Act, any transfer by operation`
  line `of law or by, or in execution of, a decree or order of a Court of competent jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `and nothing in the second Chapter of this Act shall be deemed to affect any rule of ^1*** Muhammadan ^2*** law.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "Hindu" omitted by s. 3, ibid.`
  line `2. The words "or Buddhist" omitted by s. 3, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (44101)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Interpretation-clause.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44101&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is something repugnant in the subject or`
  line context,--
  line
  line `"immoveable property" does not include standing timber, growing crops or grass; "instrument",`
  line `means a non-testamentary instrument;`
  line
  line `^1 ["attested", in relation to an instrument, means and shall be deemed always to have`
  line `meant attested by two or more witnesses each of whom has seen the executant sign or affix`
  line `his mark to the instrument, or has seen some other person sign the instrument in the`
  line `presence and by the direction of the executant, or has received from the executant a personal`
  line `acknowledgement of his signature or mark, or of the signature of such other person, and`
  line `each of whom has signed the instrument in the presence of the executant; but it shall not be`
  line `necessary that more than one of such witnesses shall have been present at the same time, and`
  line `no particular form of attestation shall be necessary;]`
  line
  line `"registered" means registered in ^2[^3[any part of the territories] to which this Act extends]`
  line `under the laws^4 for the time being in force regulating the registration of documents;`
  line
  line `"attached to the earth" means--`
  line
  line `(a) rooted in the earth, as in the case of trees and shrubs;`
  line
  line `(b) imbedded in the earth, as in the case of walls or buildings; or`
  line
  line `(c) attached to what is so imbedded for the permanent beneficial enjoyment of that to which it is`
  line attached;
  line
  line `^5["actionable claim" means a claim to any debt, other than a debt secured by mortgage of immoveable property or by hypothecation or pledge of moveable property, or to any beneficial`
  line `interest in moveable property not in the possession, either actual or constructive, of the claimant,`
  line `which the Civil Courts recognise as affording grounds for relief, whether such debt or beneficial`
  line `interest be existent, accuring, conditional or contingent;]`
  line
  line `^6["a person is said to have notice"] of a fact when he actually knows that fact, or when, but for wilful`
  line `abstention from an enquiry or search which he ought to have made, or gross negligence, he would have`
  line `known it.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--Where any transaction relating to immovable property is required by law to be`
  line `and has been effected by a registered instrument, any person acquiring such property or any part of,`
  line `or share or interest in, such property shall be deemed to have notice of such instrument as from the`
  line `date of registration or, ^7[where the property is not all situated in one sub-district, or where the`
  line `registered instrument has been registered under sub-section (2) of section 30 of the Indian`
  line `Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), from the earliest date on which any memorandum of such`
  line `registered instrument has been filed by any Sub-Registrar within whose sub-district any part of the`
  line `property which is being acquired, or of the property wherein a share or interest is being acquired, is`
  line `situated:]`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(1) the instrument has been registered and its registration completed in the manner`
  line `prescribed by the Indian. Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908) and the rules made thereunder,`
  line
  line `(2) the instrument ^8[or memorandum] has been duly entered or filed, as the case may be, in`
  line `books kept under section 51 of that Act, and`
  line
  line `(3) the particulars regarding the transaction to which the instrument relates have been correctly`
  line `entered in the indexes kept under section 55 of that Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--Any person acquiring any immoveable property or any share or interest in`
  line `any such property shall be deemed to have notice of the title, if any, of any person who is for the`
  line `time being in actual possession thereof.`
  line
  line `Explanation III.--A person shall be deemed to have had notice of any fact if his agent acquires`
  line `notice thereof whilst acting on his behalf in the course of business to which that fact is material:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the agent fraudulently conceals the fact, the principal shall not be charged`
  line `with notice thereof as against any person who was a party to or otherwise cognizant of the fraud.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1926, s. 2, as amended by Act 10 of 1927, s. 2 and Sch. 1.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for a Part A State or a Part C State (w.e.f. 1 -4-1951).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order 1956, for any State.`
  line
  line `4. See the Indian Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 2 of 1900, s. 2.`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 4, for certain words.`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 5 of 1930, s. 2, for certain words.`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by s. 2, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (44247)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Enactments relating to contracts to be taken as part of Contract Act and supplemental to the Registration Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44247&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Chapters and sections of this Act which relate to contracts shall be taken as part`
  line `of the Indian Contract Act, 1872 (9 of 1872):`
  line
  line `^1[And sections 54, paragraphs 2 and 3, 59, 107 and 123, shall be read as supplemental to the Indian`
  line `Registration Act,`
  line `^2[1908 (16 of 1908).]]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Added by Act 3 of 1885, s. 3.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 5, for "1877".`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (44102)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `“Transfer of property” defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44102&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1In the following sections transfer of property means an act`
  line `by .which a living person conveys property, in present or in future, to one or more other living persons, or`
  line `to himself, ^2[or it himself] and one or more other living persons; and "to transfer property" is to perform`
  line `such act.`
  line
  line `^3[in this section "living person" includes a company or association or body of individuals,`
  line `whether incorporated or not, but nothing herein contained shall affect any law for the time being in`
  line `force relating to transfer of property to or by companies, associations or bodies of individuals.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Nothing in Chapter II is to be deemed to affect any rule of Muhammandan law--see s. 2, supra`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 6.`
  line
  line `3. Added by s. 6, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (44103)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `What may be transferred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44103&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Property of any kind may be transferred, except as otherwise`
  line `provided by this Act or by any other law for the time being in force:`
  line
  line `(a) The chance of an heir-apparent succeeding to an estate, the chance of a relation obtaining a`
  line `legacy on the death of a kinsman, or any other mere possibility of a like nature, cannot be transferred.`
  line
  line `(b) A mere right of re-entry for breach of a condition subsequent cannot be transferred`
  line `to any one except the owner of the property affected thereby .`
  line
  line `(c) An easement cannot be transferred apart from the dominant heritage.`
  line
  line `(d) An interest in property restricted in its enjoyment to the owner personally cannot be`
  line `transferred by him.`
  line
  line `^1[(dd) A right to future maintenance, in whatsoever manner arising, secured or determined, cannot`
  line `be transferred.]`
  line
  line `(e) A mere right to sue ^2*** cannot be transferred.`
  line
  line `(f) A public office cannot be transferred, nor can the salary of a public officer, whether before or`
  line `after it has become payable.`
  line
  line `(g) Stipends allowed to military, ^3[naval], ^4[air-force] and civil pensioners of ^5[the Government] Government] and political pensions cannot be transferred.`
  line
  line `(h) No transfer can be made (1) in so far as it opposed to the nature of the interest`
  line `affected thereby, or] (2)`
  line `^6[an unlawful object or consideration within the meaning of section`
  line `23 of the Indian Contract Act, 1872 (9 of 1872), or (3) to a person legally disqualified to be`
  line transferee.]
  line
  line `^7[(i) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to authorise a tenant having an untransferable`
  line `right of occupancy, the farmer of an estate in respect of which default has been made in paying`
  line `revenue, or the lessee of an estate under the management of a court of Wards, to assign his interest`
  line `as such tenant, farmer or lessee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid.`
  line
  line `2. The words "for compensation for a fraud or for harm illegally caused" omitted by Act 2 of 1900, s. 3.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 35 of 1934, s. 2 and the Schedule.`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 10 of 1927, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `5. The word "Government" successively adapted by the A.O. 1937 and the A.O. 1950 to read as above.`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 2 of 1900, s. 3, for "for an illegal purpose".`
  line
  line `7. Added by Act 3 of 1885, s. 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (44104)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Persons competent to transfer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44104&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Every person competent to contract and entitled to transferable`
  line `property, or authorised to dispose of transferable property not his own, is competent to transfer such`
  line `property either wholly or in part and either absolutely or conditionally, in the circumstances, to the extent`
  line `and in the manner, allowed and prescribed by any law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (44105)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Operation of transfer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44105&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Unless a different intention is expressed or necessarily`
  line `implied, a transfer of property passes forthwith to the transferee all the interest which the`
  line `transferor is then capable of passing in the property, and in the legal incidents thereof.`
  line
  line `Such incidents include, where the property is land, the easements annexed thereto, the rents and`
  line `profits thereof accruing after the transfer, and all things attached to the earth;`
  line
  line `and, where the property is machinery attached to the earth, the moveable parts`
  line thereof;
  line
  line `and, where the property is a house, the easements annexed thereto, the rent thereof`
  line `accruing after the transfer, and the locks, keys, bars, doors, windows and all other things`
  line `provided for permanent use therewith;`
  line
  line `and, where the property is a debt or other actionable claim, the securities therefor`
  line `(except where they are also for other debts or claims not tr ansferred to the transferee), but`
  line `not arrears of interest accured before the transfer;`
  line
  line `and, where the property is money or other property yielding income, the interest or income thereof`
  line `accruing after the transfer takes effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (44106)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Oral transfer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44106&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `A transfer of property may be made without writing in every case`
  line `in which a writing is not expressly required by law.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (44107)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Condition restraining alienation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44107&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Where property is transferred subject to a`
  line `condition or limitation absolutely restraining the transferee or any person claiming under him`
  line `from parting with or disposing of his interest in the property, the condition or limitation is`
  line `void, except in the case of a lease where the condition is for the benefit of the lessor or those`
  line `claiming under him: provided that property may be transferred to or for the benefit of a`
  line `woman (not being a Hindu, Muhammadan or Buddhist), so that she shall not have power`
  line `during her marriage to transfer or charge the same or her beneficial interest therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (44108)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Restriction repugnant to interest cleated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 8, for the second paragraph.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44108&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Where, on a transfer of property, an`
  line `interest therein is created absolutely in favour of any person, but the terms of the transfer`
  line `direct that such interest shall be applied or enjoyed by him in a particular manner, he shall be`
  line `entitled to receive and dispose of such interest as if there were no such direction.`
  line
  line `^1[Where any such direction has been made in respect of one piece of immoveable property property for the purpose of securing the beneficial enjoyment of another piece of such property, nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect any right which the transferor may have to enforce such direction or any remedy which he may have in respect of a breach`
  line thereof.]
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (44109)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Condition making interest determinable on insolvency or attempted alienation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44109&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Where property is transferred subject to a condition or limitation making any`
  line `interest therein, reserved or given to or for the benefit of any person, to cease on his becoming`
  line `insolvent or endeavouring to transfer or dispose of the same, such condition or limitation is`
  line void.
  line
  line `Nothing in this section applies to a condition in a lease for the benefit of the lessor or those claiming`
  line `under him.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (44110)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Transfer for benefit of unborn person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44110&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Where, on a transfer of property, an`
  line `interest therein is created for the benefit of a person not in existence at the date of the`
  line `transfer, subject to a prior interest created by the same transfer, the interest created for the benefit of such person shall not take effect, unless it extends to the whole of the remaining`
  line `interest of the transferor in the property.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A transfers property of which he is the owner to B in trust for A and his intended wife succesively for their lives, and, after`
  line `the death of the survivor for the eldest son of the intended marriage for life, and after his death for A's second son. The interest so`
  line `created for the benefit of the eldest son does not take effect, because it does not extend to the whole of A's remaining interest in`
  line `the property.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (44111)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Rule against, perpetuity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44111&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `No transfer of property can operate to create an interest which is to`
  line `take effect after the lifetime of one or more persons living at the date of such transfer, and the`
  line `minority of some person who shall be in existence at the expiration of that period, and to whom, if he`
  line `attains full age, the interest created is to belong.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (44112)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Transfer to class some of whom come under sect ions 13 and 14.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 9, for "as regards the whole class".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44112&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `If, on a transfer of property,`
  line `an interest therein is created for the benefit of a class of persons with regard to some of whom such`
  line `interest fails by reason of any of the rules contained in sections 13 and 14; such interest fails ^1[in regard`
  line `to those persons only and not in regard to the whole class.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (44113)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Transfer to take effect on failure of prior interest .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `35. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for sections 16, 17 and 18.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44113&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. Transfer to take effect on failure of prior interest.-- Where, by reason of any of the`
  line `rules contained in sections 13 and 14, an interest created for the benefit of a person or of a class`
  line `of persons fails in regard to such person or the whole of such class, any interest created in the`
  line `same transaction and intended to take effect after or upon failure of such prior interest also fails.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (44114)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Direction for accumulation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for sections 16, 17 and 18.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44114&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1[17. Direction for accumulation.-- (1) Where the terms of a transfer of property direct that the`
  line `income arising from the property shall be accumulated either wholly or in part during a period longer`
  line than--
  line
  line `(a) the life of the transferor, or`
  line
  line `(b) a period of eighteen years from the date of the transfe ,`
  line
  line `such direction shall, save as hereinafter provided, be void to the extent to which the period during`
  line `which the accumulation is directed exceeds the longer of the aforesaid periods, and at the end of`
  line `such last-mentioned period the property and the income thereof shall be disposed of as if the`
  line `period during which the accumulation has been directed to be made had elapsed.`
  line
  line `(2) This section shall not affect any direction for accumulation for the purpose of--`
  line
  line `(i) the payment of the debts of the transferor or any other person taking any interest under the`
  line `transfer, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the provision of portions for children or remoter issue of the transferor or of any other person`
  line `taking any interest under the transfer, or`
  line
  line `(iii) the preservation or maintenance of the property transferred;`
  line
  line `and such direction may be made accordingly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (44115)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Transfer in perpetuity for benefit of public.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for sections 16, 17 and 18.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44115&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `^1[18. Transfer in perpetuity for benefit of public.-- The restrictions in sections 14, 16 and 17`
  line `shall not apply in the case of a transfer of property for the benefit of the public in the advancement of`
  line `religion, knowledge, commerce, health, safety, or any other object beneficial to mankind.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (44116)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Vested interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44116&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Where, on a transfer of property, an interest therein is created in favour`
  line `of a person without specifying the time when it is to take effect, or in terms specifying that it is to`
  line `take effect forthwith or on the happening of an event which must happen, such interest is vested,`
  line `unless a contrary intention appears from the terms of the transfer.`
  line
  line `A vested interest is not defeated by the death of the transferee before he obtains possession.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- An intention that an interest shall not be vested is not to be inferred merely from`
  line `a provision whereby the enjoyment thereof is postponed, or whereby a prior interest in the same property is given or reserved to some other person, or whereby income arising from the property is`
  line `directed to be accumulated until the time of enjoyment arrives, or from a provision that if a`
  line `particular event shall happen the interest shall pass to another person.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (44117)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `When unborn person acquires vested interest on transfer for his benef it .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44117&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Where, on`
  line `a transfer of property, an interest therein is created for the benefit of a person not then living, he`
  line `acquires upon his birth, unless a contrary intention appear from the terms of the transfer, a vested`
  line `interest, although he may not be entitled to the enjoyment thereof immediately on his birth.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (44118)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Contingent interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44118&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Where, on a transfer of property, an interest therein is created in`
  line `favour of a person to take effect only on the happening of a specified uncertain event, or if a`
  line `specified uncertain event shall not happen, such person thereby acquires a contingent interest in`
  line `the property. Such interest becomes a vested interest, in the former case, on the happening of the`
  line `event, in the latter, when the happening of the event becomes impossible.`
  line
  line `Exception.-- Where, under a transfer of property, a person becomes entitled to an interest`
  line `therein upon attaining a particular age, and the transferor also gives to him absolutely the income`
  line `to arise from such interest before he reaches that age, or directs the income or so much thereof as`
  line `may be necessary to be applied for his benefit, such interest is not contingent.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (44119)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Transfer to members of a class who attain a particular age.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44119&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Where, on a transfer of`
  line `property, an interest therein is created in favour of such members only of a class as shall attain a`
  line `particular age, such interest does not vest in any member of the class who has not attained that age.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (44120)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Transfer contingent on happening of specified uncertain event.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44120&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Where, on a transfer of`
  line `property, an interest therein is to accrue to a specified person if a specified uncertain event shall`
  line `happen, and no time is mentioned for the occurrence of that event, the interest fails unless such`
  line `event happens before, or at the same time as, the intermediate or precedent interest ceases to exist.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (44121)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Transfer to such of certain persons as survive at some period not specified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44121&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Where, on`
  line `a transfer of property, an interest therein is to accrue to such of certain persons as shall be surviving`
  line `at some period, but the exact period is not specified, the interest shall go to such of them as shall be`
  line `alive when the intermediate or precedent interest ceases to exist, unless a contrary intention appears`
  line `from the terms of the transfer.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A transfers property to B for life, and after his death to C and D, equally to be divided between them, or to the`
  line `survivor of them. C dies during the life of B. D survives B. At B's death the property passes to D.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (44122)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Conditional transfer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44122&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `An interest created on a transfer of property and dependent upon a`
  line `condition fails if the fulfilment of the condition is impossible, or is forbidden by law, or is of such a`
  line `nature that, if permitted, it would defeat the provisions of any law, or is fraudulent, or involves or`
  line `implies injury to the person or property of another, or the Court regards it as immoral or opposed to`
  line `public policy.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) lets a farm to B on condition that he shall walk a hundred miles in an hour. The lease is void.`
  line
  line `(b) A gives Rs. 500 to B on condition that he shall marry A's daughter C. At the date of the transfer C was dead. The`
  line `transfer is void.`
  line
  line `(c) A transfers Rs. 500 to B or. condition that she shall murder C. The transfer is void.`
  line
  line `(d) A transfer Rs. 500 to his nece C if she will desert her husband. The transfer is void.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (44123)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Fulfilment of condition precedent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44123&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Where the terms of a transfer of property impose a`
  line `conditions to be fulfilled before a person can take an interest in the property, the condition shall be`
  line `deemed to have been substantially complied with.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A transfers Rs. 5,000 to B on condition that he shall marry with the consent of C, D, and E. E dies. B marries with`
  line `the consent of C and D. B is deemed to have fulfilled the condition.`
  line
  line `(b) A transfers Rs. 5,000 to B on condition that he shall marry with the consent of C, D and E.B marries without the`
  line `consent of C, D and E, but obtains their consent after the marriage. B has not fulfilled the condition.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (44246)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Conditional transfer to one person coupled with transfer to another on failure of prior disposition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44246&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Where, on a transfer of property, an interest therein is created in favour of one person, and`
  line `by the same transaction an ulterior disposition of the same interest is made in favour of another, if the`
  line `prior disposition under the transfer shall fail, the ulterior disposition shall take effect upon the failure of`
  line `the prior disposition, although the failure may not have occurred in the manner contemplated by the`
  line transferor.
  line
  line `But, where the intention of the parties to the transaction is that the ulterior disposition shall take effect`
  line `only in the event of the prior disposition failing in a particular manner, the ulterior disposition shall not`
  line `take effect unless the prior disposition fails in that manner.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A transfers Rs. 500 to B on condition that he shall execute a certain lease within three months after As death, and,`
  line `if he should neglect to do so, to C. B dies in A's life-time. The disposition in favour of C takes effect.`
  line
  line `(b) A transfers property to his wife; but, in case she should die in his life-time, transfers to B that which he had`
  line `transferred to her. A and his wife perish together, under circumstances which make it impossible to prove that she died`
  line `before him. The disposition in favour of B does not take effect`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (44125)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Ulterior transfer conditional on happening or not happening of specified event.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44125&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `On a transfer`
  line `of property an interest therein may be created to accrue to any person with the condition superadded that`
  line `in case a specified uncertain event shall happen such interest shall pass to another person, or that in case a`
  line `specified uncertain event shall not happen such interest shall pass to another person. In each case the`
  line `dispositions are subject to the rules contained in sections 10, 12, 21, 22, 23, 24, 25 and 27.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (44126)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Fulfilment of condition subsequent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44126&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `An ulterior disposition of the kind contemplated by the`
  line `last preceding section cannot, take effect unless the condition is strictly fulfilled.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `A transfers Rs. 500 to B, to be paid to him on his attaining his majority or marrying, with a proviso that, if B dies a`
  line `minor or marries without C's consent, the Rs. 500 shall go to D. B marries when only 17 years of age, without C's consent.`
  line `The transfer to D takes effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (44127)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Prior disposition not affected by invalidity of ulterior disposition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44127&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `If the ulterior disposition`
  line `is not valid, the prior disposition is not affected by it.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `A transfers a farm to B for her life, and, if she do not desert her husband to C. B is entitled to the farm during her life as`
  line `if no condition had been inserted.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (44248)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Condition that transfer shall cease to have effect in case specified uncertain event happens or does not happen.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44248&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 12, on a transfer of property an interest therein`
  line `may be created with the condition superadded that it shall cease to exist in case a specified uncertain`
  line `event shall happen, or in case a specified uncertain event shall not happen.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A transfers a farm to B for his life, with a proviso that, in case B cuts down a certain wood, the transfer shall cease`
  line `to have any effect. B cuts down the wood. He loses his life-interest in the farm.`
  line
  line `(b) A transfers a farm to B, provided that, if B shall not go to England within three years after the date of the transfer,`
  line `his interest in the farm shall cease. B does not go to England within the term prescribed. His interest in the farm ceases.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (44129)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Such condition must not be invalid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44129&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `In order that a condition that an interest shall cease to exist`
  line `may be valid, it is necessary that the event to which it relates be one which could legally constitute the`
  line `condition of the creation of an interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (44130)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Transfer conditional on performance of act, no time being specified for performance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44130&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Where, on`
  line `a transfer of property, an interest therein is created subject to a condition that the person taking it shall`
  line `perform a certain act, but no time is specified for the performance of the act, the condition is broken when`
  line `he renders impossible, permanently or for an indefinite period, the performance of the act.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (44131)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Transfer conditional on performance of act, time being specified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44131&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Where an act is to be`
  line `performed by a person either as a condition to be fulfilled before an interest created on a transfer of`
  line `property is enjoyed by him, or as a condition on the non-fulfillment of which the interest is to pass from him to another person, and a time is specified for the performance of the act, if such performance within`
  line `the specified time is prevented by the fraud of a person who would be directly benefited by non-fulfilment`
  line `of the condition, such further time shall as against him be allowed for performing the act as shall be`
  line `requisite to make up for the delay caused by such fraud. But if no time is specified for the performance of`
  line `the act, then, if its performance is by the fraud of a person interested in the non-fulfillment of the`
  line `condition rendered impossible or indefinitely postponed, the condition shall as against him be deemed to`
  line `have been fulfilled.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (44132)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Election when necessary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44132&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Where a person professes to transfer property which he`
  line `has no right to transfer, and as part of the same transaction confers any benefit on the owner of the`
  line `property, such owner must elect either to confirm such transfer or to dissent from it; and in the latter case`
  line `he shall relinquish the benefit so conferred, and the benefit so relinquished shall revert to the transferor or`
  line `his representative as if it had not been disposed of,`
  line
  line `subject nevertheless,`
  line
  line `where the transfer is gratuitous, and the transferor has, before the election, died or otherwise become`
  line `incapable of making a fresh transfer,`
  line
  line `and in all cases where the transfer is for consideration,`
  line
  line `to the charge of making good to the disappointed transferee the amount or value of the property`
  line `attempted to be transferred to him.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `The farm of Sultanpur is the property of C and worth Rs. 800. A by an instrument of gift professes to transfer it to B, giving`
  line `by the same instrument Rs. 1,000 to C. C elects to retain the farm. He forfeits the gift of Rs. 1,000.`
  line
  line `In the same case, A dies before the election. His representative must out of the Rs. 1,000 pay Rs. 800 to B.`
  line
  line `The rule in the first paragraph of this section applies whether the transferor does or does not believe`
  line `that which he professes to transfer to be his own.`
  line
  line `A person taking no benefit directly under a transaction, but deriving a benefit under it indirectly, need`
  line `not elect.`
  line
  line `A person who in his one capacity takes a benefit under the transaction may in another dissent`
  line therefrom.
  line
  line `Exception to the last preceding four rules.-- Where a particular benefit is expressed to be conferred`
  line `on the owner of the property which the transferor professes to transfer, and such benefit is expressed to be`
  line `in lieu of that property, if such owner claim the property, he must relinquish the particular benefit, but he`
  line `is not bound to relinquish any other benefit conferred upon him by the same transaction.`
  line
  line `Acceptance of the benefit by the person on whom it is conferred constitutes an election by him to`
  line `confirm the transfer, if he is aware of his duty to elect and of those circumstances which would influence`
  line `the judgment of a reasonable man in making an election, or if he waives enquiry into the circumstances.`
  line
  line `Such knowledge or waiver shall, in the absence of evidence to the contrary, be presumed, if the`
  line `person on whom the benefit has been conferred has enjoyed it for two years without doing any act to`
  line `express dissent.`
  line
  line `Such knowledge of waiver may be inferred from any act of his which renders it impossible to place`
  line `the persons interested in the property professed to be transferred in the same condition as if such act had`
  line `not been done.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `A transfers to B an estate to which C is entitled, and as part of the same transaction gives C a coal-mine. C takes possession`
  line `of the mine and exhausts it. He has thereby confirmed the transfer of the estate to B.`
  line
  line `If he does not within one year after the date of the transfer signify to the transferor or his`
  line `representatives his intention to confirm or to dissent from the transfer, the transferor or his representative`
  line `may, upon the expiration of that period, require him to make his election; and, if he does not comply with such requisition within a reasonable time after he has received it, he shall be deemed to have elected to`
  line `confirm the transfer.`
  line
  line `In case of disability, the election shall be postponed until the disability ceases, or until the election is`
  line `made by some competent authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (44133)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Apportionment of periodical payments on determination of interest of person entitled.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44133&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `In the`
  line `absence of a contract or local usage to the contrary, all rents annuities, pensions, dividends and other`
  line `periodical payments in the nature of income shall, upon the transfer of the interest of the person entitled to`
  line `receive such payments, be deemed, as between the transferor and the transferee, to accrue due from day to`
  line `day, and to be apportion able accordingly, but to be payable on the days appointed for the payment`
  line thereof.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (44134)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Apportionment of benefit of obligation on severance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44134&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `When, in consequence of a transfer,`
  line `property is divided and held in several shares, and thereupon the benefit of any obligation relating to the`
  line `property as a whole passes from one to several owners of the property, the corresponding duty shall, in`
  line `the absence of a contract to the contrary amongst the owners, be performed in favour of each of such`
  line `owners in proportion to the value of his share in the property, provided that the duty can be severed and`
  line `that the severance does not substantially increase the burden of the obligation; but if the duty cannot be`
  line `severed, or if the severance would substantially increase the burden of the obligation the duty shall be`
  line `performed for the benefit of such one of the several owners as they shall jointly designate for that`
  line `purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person on whom the burden of the obligation lies shall be answerable for failure to`
  line `discharge it in manner provided by this section, unless and until he has had reasonable notice of the`
  line severance.
  line
  line `Nothing in this section applies to leases for agricultural purposes unless and until the State`
  line `Government by notification in the Official Gazette so directs.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A sells to B, C and D a house situated in a village and leased to E at an annual rent of Rs. 30 and delivery of one fat`
  line `sheep, B having provided half the purchase-money and C and D one quarter each. E, having notice of this, must pay Rs. 15 to B,`
  line `Rs. 7.50 to C, and Rs. 7.50 to D, and must deliver the sheep according to the Joint direction of B, C and D.`
  line
  line `(b) In the same case, each house in the village being bound to provide ten days' labour each year on a duke to prevent`
  line `inundation E had agreed as a term of his lease to perform this work for A. B, C and D severally require E to perform the ten days'`
  line `work due on account of the house of each. E is not bound to do more than ten days' work in all, according to such directions as B,`
  line `C and D may join in giving.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (44135)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Transfer by person authori sed only under certain circumstances to transfer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44135&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Where any`
  line `person, authorised only under circumstances in their nature variable to dispose of immoveable property,`
  line `transfers such property for consideration, alleging the existence of such circumstances, they shall, as`
  line `between the transferee on the one part and the transferor and other persons (if any) affected by the transfer`
  line `on the other part, be deemed to have existed, if the transferee, after using reasonable care to ascertain the`
  line `existence of such circumstances, has acted in good faith.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `A, a Hindu widow, whose husband has left collateral heirs, alleging that the property held by her as such is insufficient for`
  line `her maintenance, agrees, for purposes neither religious nor charitable, to sell a field, part of such property, to B. B satisfies`
  line `himself by reasonable enquiry that the income of the property is insufficient for A's maintenance, and that the sale of the field is`
  line `necessary, and acting in good faith, buys the field from A. As between B on the one part and A and the collateral heirs on the`
  line `other part, a necessity for the sale shall be deemed to have existed.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (44136)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Transfer where third person is entitled to maintenance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44136&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Where a third person has a right to`
  line `receive maintenance, or a provision for advancement or marriage, from the profits of immoveable`
  line `property, and such property is transferred ^1*** the right may be enforced against the transferee, if he has`
  line `notice ^2[thereof] or if the transfer is gratuitous; but not against a transferee for consideration and without`
  line `notice of the right, nor against such property in his hands.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "with the intention of defeating such right" omitted by Act 20 of 1929, s. 11.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "of such intention".`
  line
  line `3. The Illustrations omitted by Act 20 of 1929, s. 11.`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (44249)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Burden of obligation imposing restriction on use of land, or of obligation annexed to ownership but not amounting to interest or easement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for "of the latter property or to compel its enjoyment in a particular manner".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44249&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Where, for the more beneficial`
  line `enjoyment of his own immoveable property, a third person has, independently of any interest in the`
  line `immoveable property of another or of any easement thereon, a right to restrain the enjoyment ^1[in a`
  line `particular manner of the latter property], or`
  line
  line `Or of obligation annexed to ownership but not amounting to interest or easement.-- Where a`
  line `third person is entitled to the benefit of an obligation arising out of contract and annexed to the ownership`
  line `of immoveable property, but not amounting to an interest therein or easement thereon,`
  line
  line `such right or obligation may be enforced against a transferee with notice thereof or a gratuitous`
  line `transferee of the property affected thereby, but not against a transferee for consideration and without`
  line `notice of the right or obligation, nor against such property in his hands.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A contracts to sell Sultanpur to B. While the contract is still in force he sells Sultanpur to C, who has notice of the contract.`
  line `B may enforce the contract against C to the same extent as against A.`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (44138)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Transfer by ostensible owner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44138&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Where, with the consent, express or implied, of the persons`
  line `interested in immoveable property, a person is the ostensible owner of such property and transfers the`
  line `same for consideration, the transfer shall not be violable on the ground that the transferor was not`
  line `authorised to make it:`
  line
  line `Provided that the transferee, after taking reasonable care to ascertain that the transferor had power to`
  line `make the transfer, has acted in good faith.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (44139)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Transfer by person having authority to revoke former transfer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44139&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Where a person transfers`
  line `any immoveable property, reserving power to revoke the transfer, and subsequently transfers the property`
  line `for consideration to another transferee, such transfer operates in favour of such transferee (subject to any`
  line `condition attached to the exercise of the power) as a revocation of the former transfer to the extent of the`
  line power.
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A lets a house to B, and reserves power to revoke the lease if, in the opinion of a specified surveyor, B should make a use of`
  line `it detrimental to its value. Afterwards a, thinking that such a use has been made, lets the house to C. This operates as a revocation`
  line `of B's lease subject to the opinion of the surveyor as to B's use of the house having been detrimental to its value.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (44250)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Transfer by unauthorised person who subsequently acquires interest in property transferred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 13, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44250&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Where a person ^1[fraudulently or] erroneously represents that he is authorised to transfer`
  line `certain immovable property and professes to transfer such property for consideration, such transfer shall,`
  line `at the option of the transferee, operate on any interest which the transferor may acquire in such property at`
  line `any time during which the contract of transfer subsists.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section shall impair the right of transferees in good faith for consideration without`
  line `notice of the existence of the said option.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A, a Hindu who has separated from his father B, sells to C three fields, X, Y and Z, representing that A is authorised to`
  line `transfer the same. Of these fields Z does not belong to A, it having been retained by B on the partition; but on B's dying A as heir`
  line `obtains Z.C, not having rescinded the contract of sale, may require A to deliver Z to him .`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (44141)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Transfer by one co-owner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44141&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Where one of two or more co-owners of immoveable property`
  line `legally competent in that behalf transfers his share of such property or any interest therein, the transferee`
  line `acquires as to such share or interest, and so far as is necessary to give, effect to the transfer, the`
  line `transferor's right to joint possession or other common or part enjoyment of the property, and to enforce a`
  line `partition of the same, but subject to the conditions and liabilities affecting, at the date of the transfer, the`
  line `share or interest so transferred.`
  line
  line `Where the transferee of a share of a dwelling-house belonging to an undivided family is not a`
  line `member of the family, nothing in this section shall be deemed to entitle him to joint possession or other`
  line `common or part enjoyment of the house.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (44142)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Joint transfer for consideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44142&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Where immoveable property is transferred for consideration`
  line `to two or more persons and such consideration is paid out of a fund belonging to them in common, they`
  line `are, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, respectively entitled to interests in such property`
  line `identical, as nearly as may be, with the interests to which they were respectively entitled in the fund; and,`
  line `where such consideration is paid out of separate funds belonging to them respectively, they are, in the`
  line `absence of a contract to the contrary, respectively entitled to interests in such property in proportion to the`
  line `shares of the consideration which they respectively advanced.`
  line
  line `In the absence of evidence as to the interests in the fund to which they were respectively entitled, or`
  line `as to the shares which they respectively advanced, such persons shall be presumed to be equally interested`
  line `in the property.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (44143)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Transfer for consideration by persons having distinct interests.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44143&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Where immoveable property`
  line `is transferred for consideration by persons having distinct interests therein, the transferors are, in the`
  line `absence of a contract to the contrary, entitled to share in the consideration equally, where their interests in`
  line `the property were of equal value, and, where such interests were of unequal value, proportionately to the`
  line `value of their respective interests.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `(a) A, owing a moiety, and B and C, each a quarter share, of mauza Sultanpur, exchange an eighth share of that mauza for a`
  line `quarter share of mauza Lalpura. There being no agreement to the contrary, A is entitled to an eighth share in Lalpura, and B and`
  line `C each to a sixteenth share in that mauza.`
  line
  line `(b) A, being entitled to a life-interest in mauza Atrali and B and C to the reversion, sell the mauza for Rs. 1,000. A's lifeinterest is ascertained to be worth Rs. 600, the reversion Rs. 400. A is entitled to receive Rs. 600 out of the purchase-money. B`
  line `and C to receive Rs. 4000.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `(a) a Cowing a moiety, and B and C, each a quarter share, of mauza Sultanpur exchange an eighth share of that mauza for a`
  line `quarter share of mauza Lalpura. There being no agreement to the contrary, A is entitled to an eighth share in Lalpura, and B and`
  line `C each to a sixteenth share in that mauza.`
  line
  line `(b) A, being entitled to a life-interest in mauza Atrali and B and C to the reversion, sell the mauza for Rs. 1,000. A's lifeinterest is ascertained to be worth Rs. 600, the reversion Rs. 400. A is entitled to receive Rs 600 out of the purchase-money. B`
  line `and C to receive Rs. 4000.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (44144)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Transfer by co-owners of share in common property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44144&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Where several co-owners of`
  line `immoveable property transfer a share therein without specifying that the transfer is to take effect on`
  line `any particular share or shares of the transferors, the transfer, as among such transferors, takes effect`
  line `on such shares equally where the shares were equal, and where they were unequal, proprotionately to`
  line `the extent of such shares.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A, the owner of an eight-anna share, and B and C, each the owner of a four-anna share, in mauza Sultanpur, transfer a`
  line `two-anna share in the mauza to D, without specifying from which of their several shares the transfer is made. To give`
  line `effect to the transfer one-anna share is taken from the share of A, and half-an-anna share from each of the shares of B and`
  line C.
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (44145)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Priority of rights created by transfer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44145&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Where a person purports to create by transfer at`
  line `different times rights in or over the same immoveable property, and such rights cannot all exist or be`
  line `exercised to their full extent together, each later created right shall, in the absence of a special contract or`
  line `reservation binding the earlier transferees, be subject to the rights previously created.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (44146)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Transferee's right under policy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44146&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Where immoveable property is transferred for consideration,`
  line `and such property or any part thereof is at the date of the transfer insured against loss or damage by fire,`
  line `the transferee, in case of such loss or damage, may, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, require`
  line `any money which the transferor actually receives under the policy, or so much thereof as may be`
  line `necessary, to be applied in reinstating the property.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (44147)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Rent bona fide paid to holder under defective title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44147&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be chargeable with`
  line `any rents or profits of any immoveable property, which he has in good faith paid or delivered to any`
  line `person of whom he in good faith held such property, notwithstanding it may afterwards appear that the`
  line `person to whom such payment or delivery was made had no right to receive such rents or profits.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A lets a field to B at a rent of Rs. 50, and then transfers the field to C. B, having no notice of the transfer, in good faith pays`
  line `the rent to A. B is not chargeable with the rent so paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (44148)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Improvements made by bona fide holders under defective titles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44148&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `When the transferee of`
  line `immoveable property makes any improvement on the property, believing in good faith that he is`
  line `absolutely entitled thereto, and he is subsequently evicted therefrom by any person having a better`
  line `title, the transferee has a right to require the person causing the eviction either to have the value of the`
  line `improvement estimated and paid or secured to the transferee, or to sell his interest in the property to the`
  line `transferee at the then market value thereof irrespective of the value of such improvement.`
  line
  line `The amount to be paid or secured in respect of such improvement shall be the estimated`
  line `value thereof at the time of the eviction.`
  line
  line `When, under the circumstances aforesaid, the transferee has planted or sown on the property`
  line `crops which arc growing when he is evicted therefrom, he is entitled to such crops and to free`
  line `ingress and egress to gather and carry them.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (44149)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Transfer of property pending suit relating thereto.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44149&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `During the ^1[pendency] in any`
  line `Court having authority ^2[^3[within the limits] of India excluding the State of Jammu and Kashmir]`
  line `or established beyond such limits] by ^4[the Central Government ^5* * *] of ^6[any] suit or`
  line `proceeding ^7[which is not collusive and] in. which any right to immoveable property is directly`
  line `and specifically in question, the property cannot be transferred or otherwise dealt with by any`
  line `party to the suit or proceeding so as to affect the rights of any other party the reto under any`
  line `decree or order which may be made therein, except under the authority of the Court and on such`
  line `terms as it may impose.`
  line
  line `^8[Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the pendency of a suit or proceeding shall be`
  line `be deemed to commence from the date of the presentation of the plaint or the institution of the`
  line `proceeding in a Court of competent jurisdiction, and to continue until the suit or proceeding has`
  line `been disposed of by a final decree or order and complete satisfaction or discharge of such decree or order has been obtained, or has become unobtainable by reason of the expiration of any period`
  line `of limitation prescribed for the execution thereof by any law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s.14, for "active prosecution".`
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "in the Provinces or restablished beyond the limits of the Provinces".`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "within the limits of Part A States and Part C States"`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1951).`
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the Governor General in Council".`
  line `5. The words "or the Crown Representative" omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 14, for "a contentious`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 14, ibid`
  line `8. Added by 14, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (44150)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Fraudulent transfer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for section 53.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44150&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `^1[53. Fraudulent transfer.-- (1) Every transfer of immoveable property made with intent to`
  line `defeat or delay the creditors of the transferor shall be voidable at the option of any creditor so`
  line `defeated or delayed.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this sub-section shall impair the rights of a transferee in good faith and for`
  line consideration.
  line
  line `Nothing in this sub-section shall affect any law for the time being in force relating to`
  line insolvency.
  line
  line `A suit instituted by a creditor (which term includes a decree -holder whether he has or has`
  line `not applied for execution of his decree) to avoid a transfer on th e ground that it has been made`
  line `with intent to defeat or delay the creditors of the transferor, shall be instituted on behalf of, or`
  line `for the benefit of, all the creditors.`
  line
  line `(2) Every transfer of immoveable property made without consideration with intent to`
  line `defraud a subsequent transferee shall be voidable at the option of such transferee.`
  line
  line `For the purposes of this sub-section, no transfer made without consideration shall be`
  line `deemed to have been made with intent to defraud by reason only that a subsequent transfer for`
  line `consideration was made.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_a:
  sectionId (44151)
  sectionNo 53A
  orderNo 54
  title `Part performance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44151&sectionno=53A&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_53_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[53A. Part performance.-- Where any person contracts to transfer for consideration any`
  line `immoveable property by writing signed by him or on his behalf from which the terms necessary`
  line `to constitute the transfer can be ascertained with reasonable certainty,`
  line
  line `and the transferee has. in part performance of the contract, taken possession of the property or any`
  line `part thereof, or the transferee, being already in possession, continues in possession in part performance of`
  line `the contract and has done some act in furtherance of the contract,`
  line
  line `and the transferee has performed or is willing to perform his part of the contract,`
  line
  line `then, notwithstanding that ^2***, or, where there is an instrument of transfer, that the`
  line `transfer has not been completed in the manner prescribed therefor by the law for the time`
  line `being in force, the transferor or any person claiming under him shall be debarred from`
  line `enforcing against the transferee and persons claiming under him any right in respect of the`
  line `property of which the transferee has taken or continued in possession, other than a right`
  line `expressly provided by the terms of the contract:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall affect the rights of a transferee for`
  line `consideration who has no notice of the contract or of the part performance thereof.]`
obj_root_law_sections_53_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 16.`
  line
  line `1. The words "the contract though required to be registered, has not been registered, or" omitted by Act 48 of 2001, s. 10`
  line `(w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (44152)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 55
  title `“Sale” defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44152&sectionno=54&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `"Sale" is a transfer of ownership in exchange for a price paid`
  line `or promised or part-paid and part-promised.`
  line
  line `Sale how made.-- Such transfer, in the case of tangible immoveable property of the value`
  line `of one hundred rupees and upwards, or in the case of a reversion or other intangible thing,`
  line `can be made only by a registered instrument.`
  line
  line `In the case of tangible immoveable property of a va lue less than one hundred rupees,`
  line `such transfer may be made either by a registered instrument or by delivery of the`
  line property.
  line
  line `Delivery of tangible immoveable property takes place when the seller places the buyer,`
  line `or such person as he directs, in possession of the property.`
  line
  line `Contract for sale.-- A contract for the sale of immoveable property is a contract that a`
  line `sale of such property shall take place on terms settled between the parties.`
  line
  line `It does not, of itself, create any interest in or charge on such property.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam.
  line
  line `Amendment of section 54 of the Central Act 4 of 1882.--In Section 54 of the principal Act, in para 2, for the expression “by a registered instrument” the following expression shall be substituted, namely:---`
  line
  line `“by an instrument registered in the State of Assam, notwithstanding anything contained in the India Registration Act, 1908 (Act 16 of 1908) to the contrary.”`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 10 of 1976, s. 2.]`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (44153)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 56
  title `Rights and liabilities of buyer and seller.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44153&sectionno=55&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `In the absence of a contract to the`
  line `contrary, the buyer and the seller of immoveable property respectively are subject to the`
  line `liabilities, and have the rights, mentioned in the rules next following, or such of them as are`
  line `applicable to the property sold:`
  line
  line `(1) The seller is bound--`
  line
  line `(a) to disclose to the buyer any material defect in the property ^1[or in the seller's title`
  line `title thereto] of which the seller is, and the buyer is not, aware, and which the buyer`
  line `could not with ordinary care discover;`
  line
  line `(b) to produce to the buyer on his request for examination all documents of title relating to the`
  line `property which are in the seller's possession or power;`
  line
  line `(c) to answer to the best of his information all relevant questions put to him by the`
  line `buyer in respect to the property or the title thereto;`
  line
  line `(d) on payment or tender of the amount due in respect of the price, to execute a proper`
  line `conveyance of the property when the buyer tenders it to him for execution at a proper time and place;`
  line
  line `(e) between the date of the contract of sale and the delivery of the property, to take as much care`
  line `of the property and all documents of title relating thereto which are in his possession, as an owner of`
  line `ordinary prudence would take of such property and documents;`
  line
  line `(f) to give, on being so required, the buyer, or such person as he directs, such possession of the`
  line `property as its nature admits;`
  line
  line `(g) to pay all public charges and rent accrued due in respect of the property up to the`
  line `date of the sale, the interest on all incumbrances on such property due on such date, and,`
  line `except where the property is sold subject to incumbrances, to discharge all incumbrances`
  line `on the property then existing.`
  line
  line `(2) The seller shall be deemed to contract with the buyer that the interest which the seller`
  line `professes to transfer to the buyer subsists and that he has power to transfer the same .`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the sale is made by a person in a fiduciary character, he shall be`
  line `deemed to contract with the buyer that the seller has done no act whereby the property is`
  line `incumbered or whereby he is hindered from transferring it.`
  line
  line `The benefit of the contract mentioned in this rule shall be annexed to, and shall go`
  line `with, the interest of the transferee as such, and may be enforced by every person in whom`
  line `that interest is for the whole or any part thereof from time to time vested.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the whole of the purchase-money has been paid to the seller, he is also bound to`
  line `deliver to the buyer all documents of title relating to the property which are in the seller's`
  line `possession or power:`
  line
  line `Provided that, (a) where the seller retains any part of the property comprised in such`
  line `documents, he is entitled to retain them all, and, (b) where the whole of such property is sold`
  line `to different buyers the buyers,`
  line `of the lot of greatest value is entitled to such documents. But in`
  line `case (a) the seller, and in case (b) the buyer of the lot of greatest value, is bound, upon every`
  line `reasonable request by the buyer, or by any of the other buyers, as the case may be, and at the`
  line `cost of the person making the request, to produce the said documents and furnish such true`
  line `copies thereof or extracts therefrom as he may require; and in the meantime, the seller, or the`
  line `buyer, of the lot of greatest value, as the case may be, shall keep the said documents safe,`
  line `uncancelled and undefaced, unless prevented from so doing by fire or other inevitable accident.`
  line
  line `(4) The seller is entitled--`
  line
  line `(a) to the rents and profits of the property till the ownership thereof passes to the`
  line buyer;
  line
  line `(b) where the ownership of the property has passed to the buyer before payment of the`
  line `whole of the purchase-money, to a charge upon the property in the hands of the buyer,`
  line `^2[any transferee without consideration or any transferee, with notice of the non-payment], for the amount of the purchase-money, or any part thereof remaining unpaid, and for`
  line `interest on such amount or part ^2[from the date on which possession has been delivered].`
  line
  line `(5) The buyer is bound--`
  line
  line `(a) to disclose to the seller any fact as to the nature or extent of the seller's interest in the`
  line `property of which the buyer is aware, but of which he has reason to believe that the seller is`
  line `not aware, and which materially increases the value of such interest;`
  line
  line `(b) to pay or tender, at the time and place of completing the sale, the purchase -money to`
  line `the seller or such person, as he directs: provided that, where the property is sold free from`
  line `incumbrances, the buyer may retain out of the purchase-money the amount of any`
  line `incumbrances on the property existing at the date of the sale, and shall pay the amount so retained to`
  line `the persons entitled thereto;`
  line
  line `(c) where the ownership of the property has passed to the buyer, to bear any loss arising from the`
  line `destruction, injury or decrease in value of the property not caused by the seller;`
  line
  line `(d) where the ownership of the property has passed to the buyer, as between himself and the`
  line `seller, to pay all public charges and rent which may become payable in respect of the property,`
  line `the principal moneys due on any incumbrances subject to which the property is sold, and the`
  line `interest thereon afterwards accruing due.`
  line
  line `(6) The buyer is entitled--`
  line
  line `(a) where the ownership of the property has passed to him, to the benefit of any improvement`
  line `in, or increase in value of, the property, and to the rents and profits thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) unless he has improperly declined to accept delivery of the property, to a charge on the`
  line `property, as against the seller and all persons claiming under him ^3*** to the extent of the`
  line `seller's interest in the property, for the amount of any purchase-money properly paid by the`
  line `buyer in anticipation of the delivery and for interest on such amount; and, when he properly`
  line `declines to accept the delivery, also for the earnest (if any) and for the costs (if any) awarded to`
  line `him of a suit to compel specific performance of the contract or to obtain a decree for its`
  line rescission.
  line
  line `An omission to make such disclosures as are mentioned in this section, paragraph (1), clause (a), and`
  line `paragraph (5), clause (a), is fraudulent.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 17.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 17.`
  line
  line `3. The words "with notice of the payment" omitted by Act 20 of 1929, s. 17.`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (44154)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 57
  title `Marshalling by subsequent purchaser.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for section 56.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44154&sectionno=56&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `^1[56. Marshalling by subsequent purchaser.-- If the owner of two or more properties`
  line `mortgages them to one person and then sells one or more of the properties to another person, the`
  line `buyer is, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, entitled to have the mortgage-debt satisfied`
  line `out of the property or properties not sold to him, so far as the same will extend, but not so as to`
  line `prejudice the rights of the mortgagee or persons claiming under him or any other person who has`
  line `for consideration acquired an interest in any of the properties.]`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (44155)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 58
  title `Provision by Court for incumbrances and sale freed therefrom.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44155&sectionno=57&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(a) Where immoveable`
  line `property subject to any incumbrance, whether immediately payable or not, is sold by the Court or in`
  line `execution of a decree, or out of Court, the Court may, if it thinks fit, on the application of any party`
  line `to the sale, direct or allow payment into Court,--`
  line
  line `(1) in case of an annual or monthly sum charged on the property, or of a capital sum charged on a`
  line `determinable interest in the property,--of such amount as, when invested in securities of the Central`
  line `Government, the Court considers will be sufficient, by means of the interest thereof, to keep down or`
  line `otherwise provide for that charge, and`
  line
  line `(2) in any other case of a capital sum charged on the property,--of the amount sufficient to meet`
  line `the incumbrance and any interest due thereon.`
  line
  line `But in either case there shall also be paid into Court such additional amount -`
  line `as the Court`
  line `considers will be sufficient to meet the contingency of further costs, expenses and interest, and any`
  line `other contingency, except depreciation of investments, not exceeding one -tenth part of the original`
  line `amount to be paid in, unless the Court for special reasons (which it shall record) thinks fit to`
  line `require a larger additional amount.`
  line
  line `(b) Thereupon the Court may, if it thinks fit, and after notice to the incumbrance, unless the`
  line `Court, for reasons to be recorded in writing, thinks fit to dispense with such notice, declare the`
  line `property to be freed from the incumbrance, and make any order for conveyance, or vesting order, proper for giving effect to the sale, and give directions for the retention and investment of the`
  line `money in Court.`
  line
  line `(c) After notice served on the persons interested in or entitled to the money or fund in`
  line `Court. the Court may direct payment or transfer thereof to the persons entitled to receive or`
  line `give a discharge for the same, and generally may give directions respecting the application or`
  line `distribution of the capital or income thereof.`
  line
  line `(d) An appeal shall lie from any declaration, order or direction under this section as if the same were`
  line `a decree.`
  line
  line `(e) In this section "Court" means (1) a High Court in the exercise of its ordinary or`
  line `extraordinary original civil jurisdiction, (2) the Court of a District Judge within the local limits`
  line `of whose jurisdiction the property or any part thereof is situate, (3) any other Court which the`
  line `State Government may, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette, decla re to be`
  line `competent to exercise the jurisdiction conferred by this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (44251)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 59
  title `Mortgage , mortgagor , mortgagee , mortgage-money and mortgage- deed defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44251&sectionno=58&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(a) A mortgage is the transfer of an interest in specific immoveable property for the`
  line `purpose of securing the payment of money advanced or to be advanced by way of loan, an`
  line `existing or future debt, or the performance of an engagement which may give rise to a pecuniary`
  line liability.
  line
  line `The transferor is called a mortgagor, the transferee a mortgagee; the principal money and`
  line `interest of which payment is secured for the time being arc called the mortgage -money, and`
  line `the instrument (if any) by which the transfer is effected is called a mortgage -deed.`
  line
  line `(b) Simple mortgage.-- Where, without delivering possession of the mortgaged property,`
  line `the mortgagor binds himself personally to pay the mortgage-money, and agrees, expressly or`
  line `impliedly, that, in the event of his failing to pay according to his contract, the mortgagee shall`
  line `have a right to cause the mortgaged property to be sold and the proceeds of sale to be applied,`
  line `so far as may be necessary, in payment of the mortgage-money, the transaction is called a`
  line `simple mortgage and the mortgagee a simple mortgagee.`
  line
  line `(c) Mortgage by conditional sale.-- Where the mortgagor ostensibly sells the mortgaged`
  line property--
  line
  line `on condition that on default of payment of the mortgage-money on a certain date the sale shall`
  line `become absolute, or`
  line
  line `on condition that on such payment being made the sale shall become void, or`
  line
  line `on condition that on such payment being made the buyer shall transfer the property to`
  line `the seller,`
  line
  line `the transaction is called a mortgage by conditional sale and the mortgagee a mortgagee by`
  line `conditional sale:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that no such transaction shall be deemed to be a mortgage, unless the condition is`
  line `embodied in the document which effects or purports to effect the sale.]`
  line
  line `(d) Usufructuary mortgage.-- Where the mortgagor delivers possession ^2[or expressly or by`
  line `implication binds himself to deliver possession] of the mortgaged property to the mortgagee, and`
  line `authorises him to retain such possession until payment of the mortgage -money, and to receive`
  line `the rents and profits accruing from the property ^3[or any part of such rents and profits and to`
  line `appropriate the same] in lieu of interest, or in payment of the mortgage -money, or partly in`
  line `lieu of interest ^4[or] partly in payment of the mortgage-money, the transaction is called an`
  line `usufructuary mortgage and the mortgagee an usufructuary mortgagee.`
  line
  line `(e) English mortgage.-- Where the mortgagor binds himself to repay the mortgage-money on a`
  line `certain date, and transfers the mortgaged property absolutely to the mortgagee, but subject to a proviso`
  line `that he will re-transfer it to the mortgagor upon payment of the mortgage-money as agreed, the`
  line `transaction is called an English mortgage.`
  line
  line `^5[(f) Mortgage by deposit of title-deeds.-- Where a person in any of the following towns,`
  line `namely, the towns of Calcutta, Madras ^6[and Bombay], ^7*** and in any other town which the`
  line `^8[State Government concerned] may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf,`
  line `delivers to a creditor or his agent documents of title to immoveable property, with intent to create`
  line `a security thereon, the transaction is called a mortgage by deposit of title-deeds.`
  line
  line `(g) Anomalous mortgage.-- A mortgage which is not a simple mortgage, a mortgage by`
  line `conditional sale, an usufructuary mortgage, an English mortgage or a mortgage by deposit of`
  line `title-deeds within the meaning of this section is called an anomalous mortgage.]`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Added by Act 20 of 1920 , s . 1 9 .`
  line
  line `2 . I n s . b y s . 1 9 , i b i d .`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for and to appropriate them.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 19, ibid, for and.`
  line
  line `5. Added by Act 20 of 1929, s. 19.`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for Bombay and Karachi. The word and had been ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `7. The words "Rangoon, Moulmein, Bassein and Akyab" omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `8. The words "Governor General in Council" successively amended by the A.O. 1937 and the A.O. 1950 to read`
  line `as above.`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (44157)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 60
  title `Mortgage when to be by assurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44157&sectionno=59&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Where the principal money secured is one hundred`
  line `rupees or upwards, a mortgage ^1[other than a mortgage by deposit of title-deeds], can be effected`
  line `only by a registered instrument signed by the mortgagor and attested by at least two witnesses.`
  line
  line `Where the principal money secured is less than one hundred rupees, a mortgage may be`
  line `effected either by ^2[a registered instrument] signed and attested as aforesaid, or (except in the`
  line `case of a simple mortgage) by delivery of the property.`
  line
  line `^3* * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 20.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 6 of 1904, s. 3, for "an instrument".`
  line
  line `3. Third paragraph omitted by Act 20 of 1929, s. 20.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_a:
  sectionId (44254)
  sectionNo 59A
  orderNo 61
  title `References to mortgagors and mortgagees to include persons deriving title from them.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 21, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44254&sectionno=59A&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_59_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[59A. References to mortgagors and mortgagees to include persons deriving title from`
  line `them.-- Unless otherwise expressly provided, references in this Chapter to mortgagors and`
  line `mortgagees shall be deemed to include references to persons deriving title from them`
  line respectively.]
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (44159)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 62
  title `Right of mortgagor to redeem.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44159&sectionno=60&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `At any time after the principal money has become ^1[due],`
  line `^1[due], the mortgagor has a right, on payment or tender, at a proper time and place, of the`
  line `mortgage-money, to require the mortgagee (a) to deliver ^2[to the mortgagor the mortgage-deed and`
  line `all documents relating to the mortgaged property which are in the possession or power of the`
  line `mortgagee], (b) where the mortgagee is in possession of the mortgaged property, to deliver`
  line `possession thereof to the mortgagor, and (c) at the cost of the mortgagor either to re-transfer the`
  line `mortgaged property to him or to such third person as he may direct, or to execute and (where the`
  line `mortgage has been effected by a registered instrument) to have registered an acknowledgement in`
  line `writing that any right in derogation of his interest transferred to the mortgagee has been extinguished:`
  line
  line `Provided that the right conferred by this section has not been extinguished by act of the parties or by`
  line `^3[decree] of a Court.`
  line
  line `The right conferred by this section is called a right to redeem, and a suit to enforce it is called a suit`
  line `for redemption.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section shall be deemed to render invalid any provision to the effect that, if`
  line `the time fixed for payment of the principal money has been allowed to p ass or no such time has`
  line `been fixed. the mortgagee shall be entitled to reasonable notice before payment or tender of`
  line `such money.`
  line
  line `Redemption of portion of mortgaged property.-- Nothing in this section shall entitle a`
  line `person interested in a share only of the mortgaged property to redeem his own share only, on`
  line `payment of a proportionate part of the amount remaining due on the mortgage, except ^4[only] where a mortgagee, or, if there are more mortgagees than one, all such mortgagees, has or have`
  line `acquired, in whole or in part, the share of a mortgager.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for "payable".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for "the mortgage-deed, if any, to the mortgagor".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 22, for "order".`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 22.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_a:
  sectionId (44160)
  sectionNo 60A
  orderNo 63
  title `Obligation to transfer to third party instead of re -transference to mortgagor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_a_content
  footnotes `1. Sections 60A and 60B ins. by s. 23, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44160&sectionno=60A&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_60_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[60A. Obligation to transfer to third party instead of retransference to mortgagor .-- (1) Where a mortgagor is entitled to redemption, then, on the fulfilment of any conditions on the`
  line `fulfilment of which he would be entitled to require a re-transfer, he may require the mortgagee,`
  line `instead of re-transferring the property, to assign the mortgage-debt and transfer the mortgaged`
  line `property to such third person as the mortgagor may direct; and the mortgagee shall be bound to`
  line `assign and transfer accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) The rights conferred by this section belong to and may be enforced by the mortgagor or`
  line `by any encumbrancer notwithstanding an intermediate encumbrance: but the requisition of any`
  line `encumbrancer shall prevail over a requisition of the mortgagor and, as between encumbrancers,`
  line `the requisition of a prior encumbrancer shall prevail over that of a subsequent encumbrancer.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this section do not apply in the case of a mortgagee who is or has been in`
  line possession.]
obj_root_law_sections_60_b:
  sectionId (44161)
  sectionNo 60B
  orderNo 64
  title `Right to inspection and production of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_b_content
  footnotes `1. Sections 60A and 60B ins. by s. 23, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44161&sectionno=60B&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_60_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[60B. Right to inspection and production of documents.-- A mortgagor, as long as his right`
  line `of redemption subsists, shall be entitled at all reasonable times, at his request and at his own`
  line `cost, and on payment of the mortgagee's costs and expenses in this behalf, to inspect and make`
  line `copies or abstracts of, or extracts from, documents of title relating to the mortgaged property`
  line `which arc in the custody or power of the mortgagee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (44162)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 65
  title `Right to redeem separately or simultaneously.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 24, ibid., for s. 61.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44162&sectionno=61&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `^1[61. Right to redeem separately or simultaneously.-- A mortgagor who has executed two`
  line `or more mortgages in favour of the same mortgagee shall, in the absence of a contract to the`
  line `contrary, when the principal money of any two or more of the mortgages has become due, be`
  line `entitled to redeem any one such mortgage separately, or any two or more of such mortgages`
  line together.]
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (44163)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 66
  title `Right of usufructuary mortgagor to recover possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44163&sectionno=62&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `In the case of a usufructuary`
  line `mortgage, the mortgagor has a right to recover possession of the property ^1[together with the mortgagedeed and all documents relating to the mortgaged property which are in the possession or power of the`
  line mortgagee].--
  line
  line `(a) where the mortgagee is authorised to pay himself the mortgage-money] from the`
  line `rents and profits of the property.--when such money is paid:`
  line
  line `(b) where the mortgagee is authorised to pay himself from such rents and profits ^2[or`
  line `arty part thereof a part only of the mortgage -money,]--.when the term (if any), prescribed`
  line `for the payment of the mortgage-money has expired and the mortgagor pays or tenders to`
  line `the mortgagee ^3[the mortgage-money or the balance thereof] or deposits it in Court as`
  line `hereinafter provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 25, ibid.`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for "the interest of the principal money".`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for "the principal money".`
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (44164)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 67
  title `Accession to mortgaged property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 26, for "at the same rate of interest".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44164&sectionno=63&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Where mortgaged property in possession of the`
  line `mortgagee has, during the continuance of the mortgage, received any accession, the mortgagor, upon redemption, shall, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, be entitled as`
  line `against the mortgagee to such accession.`
  line
  line `Accession acquired in virtue of transferred ownership.-- Where such accession has`
  line `been acquired at the expense of the mortgagee, and is capable of separate possession or`
  line `enjoyment without detriment to the principal property, the mortgagor desiring to take the`
  line `accession must pay to the mortgagee the expense of acquiring it. If such separate possession`
  line `or enjoyment is not possible, the accession must be delivered with the property; the`
  line `mortgagor being liable, in the case of an acquisition necessary to preserve the property from`
  line `destruction, forfeiture or sale, or made with his assent, to pay the proper c ost thereof, as an`
  line `addition to the principal money, ^1[with interest at the same rate as is payable on the`
  line `principal, or, where no such rate is fixed,`
  line `at the rate of nine per cent. per annum.]`
  line
  line `In the case last mentioned the profits, if any, arising from the accession shall be credited to the`
  line mortgagor.
  line
  line `Where the mortgage is usufructuary and the accession has been acquired at the expense`
  line `of the mortgagee, the profits, if any, arising from the accession shall, in the absence of a`
  line `contract to the contrary, be set off against interest, if any, payable on the money so`
  line expended.
obj_root_law_sections_63_a:
  sectionId (44165)
  sectionNo 63A
  orderNo 68
  title `Improvements to mortgaged property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 27, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44165&sectionno=63A&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_63_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[63A. Improvements to mortgaged property.-- (1) Where mortgaged property in possession of the mortgagee has, during the continuance of the mortgage, been improved, the`
  line `mortgagor, upon redemption, shall, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, be entitled to`
  line `the improvement; and the mortgagor shall not, save only in cases provided for in`
  line `sub-section (2), be liable to pay the cost thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any such improvement was effected at the cost of the mortgagee and was`
  line `necessary to preserve the property from destruction or deterioration or was necessary to`
  line `prevent the security from becoming insufficient, or was made in compliance with the`
  line `lawful order of any public servant or public authority, the mortgagor shall, in the absence`
  line `of a contract to the contrary, be liable to, pay the proper cost thereof as an addition to the`
  line `principal money with interest at the same rate as is payable on the principal, or, where no`
  line `such rate is fixed, at the rate of nine per cent. per annum, and the profits, if any, accruing`
  line `by reason of the improvement shall be credited to the mortgagor.]`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (44166)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 69
  title `Renewal of mortgaged lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes `1. The words "for a term of years" omitted by s. 28, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44166&sectionno=64&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `Where the mortgaged property is a lease ^1***, and`
  line `the mortgagee obtains a renewal of the lease, the mortgagor, upon redemption, shall, in the`
  line `absence of a contract by him to the contrary, have the benefit of the new lease.`
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (44167)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 70
  title `Implied contracts by mortgagor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44167&sectionno=65&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `In the absence of a contract to the contrary, the`
  line `mortgagor shall be deemed to contract with the mortgagee,--`
  line
  line `(a) that the interest which the mortgagor professes to transfer to the mortgagee`
  line `subsists, and that the mortgagor has power to transfer the same ;`
  line
  line `(b) that the mortgagor will defend, or, if the mortgagee be in possession of the`
  line `mortgaged property, enable him to defend, the mortgagor's title thereto;`
  line
  line `(c) that the mortgagor will, so long as the mortgagee is not in possession of the`
  line `mortgaged property, pay all public charges accruing due in respect of the property;`
  line
  line `(d) and, where the mortgaged property is a lease ^1***, that the rent payable under the lease,`
  line `lease, the conditions contained therein, and the contracts binding on the lessee have been paid,`
  line `performed and observed down to the commencement of the mortgage; and that the mortgagor`
  line `will, so long as the security exists and the mortgagee is not in possession of the mortgaged`
  line `property, pay the rent reserved by the lease, or, if the lease be renewed, the renewed lease,`
  line `perform the conditions contained therein and observe the contracts binding on the lessee, and indemnify the mortgagee against all claims sustained by reason of the non-payment of the said`
  line `rent or the a non-performance or non-observance of the said conditions and contracts;`
  line
  line `(e) and, where the mortgage is a second or subsequent incumbrance on the property, that`
  line `the mortgagor will pay the interest from time to time accruing due on each prior incumbrance`
  line `as and when it becomes due, and will at the proper time discharge the principal money due on`
  line `such prior incumbrance.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *.`
  line
  line `The benefit of the contracts mentioned in this section shall be annexed to and shall go with the`
  line `interest of the mortgagee as such, and may be enforced by every person in whom that interest is`
  line `for the whole or any part thereof from time to time vested.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "for a term of years" omitted by s. 29, ibid.`
  line
  line `2. Certain words omitted by Act 20 of 1929, s. 29.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_a:
  sectionId (44168)
  sectionNo 65A
  orderNo 71
  title `Mortgagor‟s power to lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 30, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44168&sectionno=65A&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_65_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[65A. Mortgagor's power to lease.-- (1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), a mortgagor,`
  line `while lawfully in possession of the mortgaged property, shall have power to make leases thereof which`
  line `shall be binding on the mortgagee.`
  line
  line `(2) (a) Every such lease shall be such as would be made in the ordinary course of management of the`
  line `property concerned, and in accordance with any local law, custom or usage.`
  line
  line `(b) Every such lease shall reserve the best rent that can reasonably be obtained, and no premium`
  line `shall be paid or promised and no rent shall be payable in advance.`
  line
  line `(c) No such lease shall contain a covenant for renewal.`
  line
  line `(d) Every such lease shall take effect from a date not later than six months from the date on which it`
  line `is made.`
  line
  line `(e) In the case of a lease of buildings, whether leased it or without the land on which they`
  line `stand, the duration of the lease shall in no case exceed three years, and the lease shall contain a`
  line `covenant for payment of the rent and a condition of re-entry on the rent not being paid within a`
  line `time therein specified.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) apply only if and as far as a contrary intention is not`
  line `expressed in the mortgage-deed; and the provisions of sub-section (2) may be varied or extended by`
  line `the mortgage-deed and, as so varied and extended, shall, as far as may be, operate in like manner and`
  line `with all like incidents, effects and consequences, as if such variations or extensions were contained in`
  line `that sub-section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (44169)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 72
  title `Waste by mortgagor in possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44169&sectionno=66&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `A mortgagor in possession of the mortgaged`
  line `property is not liable to the mortgagee for allowing the property to deteriorate; but he must not`
  line `commit any act which is destructive or permanently injurious thereto, if the security is`
  line `insufficient or will be rendered insufficient by such act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- A security is insufficient within the meaning of this section unless the value of the`
  line `mortgaged property exceeds by one-third, or, if consisting of buildings, exceeds by one-half, the amount`
  line `for the time being due on the mortgage.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (44170)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 73
  title `Right to foreclosure or sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44170&sectionno=67&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `In the absence of a contract to the contrary, the mortgagee`
  line `has, at any time after the mortgage-money has become ^1[due] to him, and before a decree has been`
  line `made for the redemption of the mortgaged property, or the mortgage-money has been paid or`
  line `deposited as hereinafter provided, a right to obtain from the Court ^2[a decree] that the mortgagor`
  line `shall be absolutely debarred of his right to redeem the property, or ^2[a decree] that the property be`
  line sold.
  line
  line `A suit to obtain ^2[a decree] that a mortgagor shall be absolutely debarred of his right to redeem the`
  line `mortgaged property is called a suit for foreclosure.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section shall be deemed--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) to authorise any mortgagee, other than a mortgagee by conditional sale or a`
  line `mortgagee under an anomalous mortgage by the terms of which he is entitled to foreclose, to`
  line `institute a suit for foreclosure, or an usufructuary mortgagee as such or a mortgagee by`
  line `conditional sale as such to institute a suit for sale; or]`
  line
  line `(b) to authorise a mortgagor who holds the mortgagee's rights as his trustee or legal`
  line `representative, and who may sue for a sale of the property, to institute a suit for foreclosure;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) to authorise the mortgagee of a railway, canal or other work in the maintenance of which the`
  line `public are interested, to institute a suit for foreclosure or sale; or`
  line
  line `(d) to authorise a person interested in part only of the mortgage-money to-institute a suit`
  line `relating only to a corresponding part of the mortgaged property, unless the mortgagees have,`
  line `with the consent of the mortgagor, severed their interests under the mortgage.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for "payable".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for "an order".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 31, for clause (a).`
obj_root_law_sections_67_a:
  sectionId (44171)
  sectionNo 67A
  orderNo 74
  title `Mortgagee when bound to bring one suit on several mortgages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 32, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44171&sectionno=67A&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_67_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[67A. Mortgagee when bound to bring one suit on several inortgages.-- A mortgagee who`
  line `holds two or more mortgages executed by the same mortgagor in respect of each of which he has a`
  line `right to obtain the same kind of decree under section 67, and who sues to obtain such decree on`
  line `any one of the mortgages, shall, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, be bound to sue on all`
  line `the mortgages in respect of which the mortgage-money has become due.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (44172)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 75
  title `Right to sue for mortgage-money.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 33, ibid., for section 68.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44172&sectionno=68&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `^1[68. Right to sue for mortgage-money.-- (1) The mortgagee has a right to sue for the mortgagemoney in the following cases and no others, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) where the mortgagor binds himself to repay the same;`
  line
  line `(b) where, by any cause other than the wrongful act or default of the mortgagor or`
  line `mortgagee, the mortgaged property is wholly or partially destroyed or the security is rendered`
  line `insufficient within the meaning of section 66, and the mortgagee has given the mortgagor a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of providing further security enough to render the whole security`
  line `sufficient, and the mortgagor has failed to do so;`
  line
  line `(c) where the mortgagee is deprived of the whole or part of his security by or in consequence of`
  line `the wrongful act or default of the mortgagor;`
  line
  line `(d) where, the mortgagee being entitled to possession of the mortgaged property, the mortgagor`
  line `fails to deliver the same to him, or to secure the possession thereof to him without disturbance by the`
  line `mortgagor or any person claiming under a title superior to that of the mortgagor:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the case referred to in clause (a), a transferee from the mortgagor or from`
  line `his legal representative shall not be liable to be sued for, the mortgage-money.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a suit is brought under clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (1), the Court may,`
  line `at its discretion, stay the suit and all proceedings therein, notwithstanding any contract to the`
  line `contrary, until the mortgagee has exhausted all his available remedies against the mortgaged`
  line `property or what remains of it, unless the mortgagee abandons his security and, if necessary,`
  line `re-transfers the mortgaged property.]`
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (44173)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 76
  title `Power of sale when valid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44173&sectionno=69&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] ^2[^3*** a mortgatee, or any person acting on his`
  line `behalf, shall, subject to the provisions of this section, have power to sell or ,concur in selling the`
  line `mortgaged property, or any part thereof, in default of payment of the mortgage -money, without`
  line `the intervention of the Court, in the following cases and in no others, namely:--]`
  line
  line `(a) where the mortgage is an English mortgage, and neither the mortgagor nor the`
  line `mortgagee is a Hindu, Muhammadan or Buddhist ^4[or a member of any other race, sect, tribe`
  line `or class from time to time specified in this behalf by ^5[the State Government], in the Official`
  line Gazette;
  line
  line `(b) where ^6[a power of sale without the intervention of the Court is expressly conferred`
  line `on the mortgagee by the mortgage-deed, and] the mortgagee is ^7[the Government];`
  line
  line `(c) where ^6[a power of sale without the intervention of the Court is expressly conferred`
  line `on the mortgagee by the mortgage-deed, and] the mortgaged property or any part thereof`
  line `^8[was, on the date of the execution of the mortgage -deed], situate within the towns of`
  line `Calcutta, Madras, Bombay, ^9[*** ^10[or in any other town or area which the State`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify' in this behalf.]`
  line
  line `^11[(2)] ^12*** No such power shall be exercised unless and until--`
  line
  line `^13[(a)] notice in writing requiring payment of the principal money has been served on the`
  line `mortgagor, or, one of several mortgagors, and default has been made in payment of the principal`
  line `money, or of part thereof, for three months after such service; or`
  line
  line `^14[(b)] some interest under the mortgage amounting at least to five hundred repees is`
  line `in arrear and unpaid for three months after becoming due.`
  line
  line `^15[(3)] When a sale has been made in professed exercise of such a power, the title of the`
  line `purchaser shall not be impeachable on the ground that no case had arisen to authorize the sale,`
  line `or that due notice was not given, or that the power was otherwise improperly or irregularly`
  line `'exercised; but any person damnified by an unauthorised, or improper, or irregular' exercise of`
  line `the power shall have his remedy in damages against the person exercising the power.`
  line
  line `^16[(4)] The money which is received by the mortgagee, arising from the sale, after discharge of`
  line `prior incumbrances, if any, to which the sale is not made subject, or after payment into Court under`
  line `section 57 of a sum to meet any prior incumbrance, shall, in the absence of a contract to the contrary,`
  line `be held by him in trust to be applied by him, first, in payment of all costs, charges and expenses`
  line `properly incurred by him as incident to the sale or any attempted sale; and, secondly, discharge of the`
  line `mortgage-money and costs and other money, if any, due under the mortgage; and the residue of the`
  line `money so received shall be paid to the person entitled to the mortgaged property, or authorised to`
  line `give receipts for the proceeds of the sale thereof.`
  line
  line `^17[(5)] Nothing in this section or in section 69A applies to powers conferred before the first day of`
  line `July, 1882.]`
  line
  line `^18* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 69 numbered as sub-section (1) of that section by Act 20 of 1929, s. 34.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 34, ibid., for certain words.`
  line
  line `3. The words Notwithstanding anything contained in the Trustees and Mortagees Powers act, 1899 (28 of 1866) omitted by`
  line `Act 48 of 1952, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 3 of 1885, s. 5.`
  line
  line `5. The words the L.G., with the previous sanction of the G. G. in C. successively adapted by the A.O. 1937 and the A.O. 1950`
  line `to read as above.`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 34.`
  line
  line `7. The words the Secretary of State for India in Council successively amended by the A.O. 1937 and the A.O. 1950`
  line `to read as above.`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 34, for is.`
  line
  line `9. The word Karachi omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
  line
  line `10. The words or Rangoon have been successively amended by Acts 6 of 1904, 11 of 1915, 20 of 1929, the A.O. 1937 and the`
  line `A.O. 1950 to read as above.`
  line
  line `11. Second paragraph numbered as sub-section (2) by Act 20 of 1929, s. 34.`
  line
  line `12. The word 'But omitted by s. 34, ibid.`
  line
  line `13. Clause (1) was lettered (a) by s. 34, ibid.`
  line
  line `14. Clause (2) was lettered (b) by s. 34, ibid.`
  line
  line `15. Third paragraph numbered as sub-section (3) by s. 34, ibid.`
  line
  line `16. Fourth paragraph numbered as sub-section (4) by Act 20 of 1929, s. 34.`
  line
  line `17. Subs. by s. 34, ibid., for fifth paragraph.`
  line
  line `18. The last paragraph of this section omitted by s. 34, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_a:
  sectionId (44174)
  sectionNo 69A
  orderNo 77
  title `Appointment of receiver.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 35.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44174&sectionno=69A&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_69_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[69A. Appointment of receiver.--(1) A mortgagee having the right to exercise a power of`
  line `sale under section 69 shall, subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), be entitled to appoint, by`
  line `writing signed by him or on his behalf, a receiver of the income of the mortgaged property or any`
  line `part thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who has been named in the mortgage-deed and is willing and able to act as receiver`
  line `may be appointed by the mortgagee.`
  line
  line `If no person has been so named, or if all persons named are unable or unwilling to act, or are`
  line `dead, the mortgagee may appoint any person to whose appointment the mortgagor agrees; failing`
  line `such agreement, the mortgagee shall be entitled to apply to the Court for the appointment of a`
  line `receiver, and any person appointed by the Court shall be deemed to have been duly appointed by`
  line `the mortgagee.`
  line
  line `A receiver may at any time be removed by writing signed by or on behalf of the mortgagee`
  line `and the mortgagor, or by the Court on application made by either party and on due cause shown.`
  line
  line `A vacancy in the office of receiver may be filled in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line sub-section.
  line
  line `(3) A receiver appointed under the powers conferred by this section shall be deemed to be the agent`
  line `of the mortgagor; and the mortgagor shall be solely responsible for the receiver's acts or defaults, unless`
  line `the mortgage-deed otherwise provides or unless such acts or defaults arc due to the improper intervention`
  line `of the mortgagee.`
  line
  line `(4) The receiver shall have power to demand and recover all the income of which he is`
  line `appointed receiver, by suit, execution or otherwise, in the name either of the mortgagor or of the`
  line `mortgagee to the full extent of the interest which the mortgagor could dispose of, and to give`
  line `valid receipts accordingly for the same, and to exercise any powers which may have been`
  line `delegated to him by the mortgagee in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(5) A person paying money to the receiver shall not be concerned to inquire if the appointment of the`
  line `receiver was valid or not.`
  line
  line `(6) The receiver shall be entitled to retain out of any money received by him, for his remuneration,`
  line `and in satisfaction of all costs, charges and expenses incurred by him as receiver, a commission at such`
  line `rate not exceeding five per cent. on the gross amount of all money received as is specified in his`
  line `appointment, and, if no rate is so specified, then at the rate of five per cent. on that gross`
  line `amount, or at such other rate as the Court thinks fit to allow, on application made by him for`
  line `that purpose.`
  line
  line `(7) The receiver shall, if so directed in writing by the mortgagee, insure to the extent, if`
  line `any, to which the mortgagee might have insured, and keep insured against loss or damage by`
  line `fire, out of the money received by him, the mortgaged property or any part thereof being of an`
  line `insurable nature.`
  line
  line `(8) Subject to the provisions of this act as to the application of insurance money, the`
  line `receiver shall apply all money received by him as follows, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) in discharge of all rents, taxes, land revenue, rates and outgoings whatever affecting the`
  line `mortgaged property;`
  line
  line `(ii) in keeping down all annual sums or other payments, and the interest on all`
  line `principal sums, having priority to the mortgage in right whereof he is receiver;`
  line
  line `(iii) in payment of his commission, and of the premiums on fire, life or other`
  line `insurances, if any, properly payable under the mortgage -deed or under this Act, and the`
  line `cost of executing necessary or proper repairs directed in writing by the mo rtgagee;`
  line
  line `(iv) in payment of the interest falling due under the mortgage;`
  line
  line `(v) in or towards discharge of the principal money, if so directed in writing by the`
  line mortgagee;
  line
  line `and shall pay the residue, if any, of the money received by him to the person who, but for the`
  line `possession of the receiver, would have been entitled to receive the income of which he is`
  line `appointed receiver, or who is otherwise entitled to the mortgaged property.`
  line
  line `(9) The provisions of sub-section (1) apply only if and as far as a contrary intention is not`
  line `expressed in the mortgage-deed; and the provisions of sub-sections (3) to (8) inclusive may be`
  line `varied or extended by the mortgage-deed, and, as so varied or extended, shall, as far as may be,`
  line `operate in like manner and with all the like incidents, effects and consequences, as if such`
  line `variations or extensions were contained in the said sub-sections.`
  line
  line `(10) Application may be made, without the institution of a suit, to the Court for its opinion,`
  line `advice or direction on any present question respecting the management or administration of the`
  line `mortgaged property, other than questions of difficulty or importance not proper in the opinion of`
  line `the Court for summary disposal. A copy of such application shall be served upon, and the hearing`
  line `thereof may be attended by, such of the persons interested in the application as the Court may`
  line `think fit.`
  line
  line `The costs of every application under this sub-section shall be in the discretion of the Court.`
  line
  line `(11) In this section, "the Court" means the Court which would have jurisdiction in a suit to enforce`
  line `the mortgage.]`
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (44175)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 78
  title `Accession to mortgaged property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44175&sectionno=70&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `If, after the date of a mortgage, any accession is`
  line `made to the mortgaged property, the mortgagee, in the absence of a contract to the co ntrary,`
  line `shall, for the purposes of the security, be entitled to such accession.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A mortgages to B a certain field bordering on a river. The field is increased by alluvion. For the purposes of his`
  line `security, B is entitled to the increase.`
  line
  line `(b) A mortgages a certain plot of building land to B and afterwards erects a house on the plot. For the purposes of his`
  line `security, B is entitled to the house as well as the plot.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (44176)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 79
  title `Renewal of mortgaged lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes `1. The words "for a term of years" omitted by Act 20 of 1929, s. 36.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44176&sectionno=71&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `When the mortgaged property is as lease ^1***, and the`
  line `mortgagor obtains a renewal of the lease, the mortgagee, in the absence of a contract to the`
  line `contrary, shall, for the purposes of the security, be entitled to the new lease.`
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (44177)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 80
  title `Rights of mortgagee in possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44177&sectionno=72&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `^1[A mortgagee] may spend such money as is`
  line necessary--
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) for ^3[the preservation of the mortgaged property] from destruction, forfeiture or`
  line sale;
  line
  line `(c) for supporting the mortgagor's title to the property;`
  line
  line `(d) for making his own title thereto good against the mortgagor; and`
  line
  line `(e) when the mortgaged property is a renewable lease-hold, for the renewal of the lease;`
  line
  line `and may, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, add such money to the principal`
  line `money, at the rate of interest payable on the principal, and, where no such rate is fixed, at`
  line `the rate of nine per cent. per annum:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that the expenditure of money by the mortgagee under clause (b) or clause`
  line `(c) shall not be deemed to be necessary unless the mortgagor has been called upon and has`
  line `failed to take proper and timely steps to preserve the property or to support the title.]`
  line
  line `Where the property is by its nature insurable, the mortgagee may also, in the abs ence`
  line `of a contract to the contrary, insure and keep insured against loss or damage by fire the`
  line `whole or any pant of such property; and the premiums paid for any such insurance shall be`
  line `^5[added to the principal money with interest at the same rate as is pay able on the principal`
  line `money or, where no such rate is fixed, at the rate of nine per cent. per annum]. But the`
  line `amount of such insurance shall not exceed the amount specified in this behalf in the`
  line `mortgage-deed or (if no such amount is therein specified) two-thirds of the amount that`
  line `would be required in case of total destruction to reinstate the property insured.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section shall be deemed to authorise the mortgagee to insure when an`
  line `insurance of the property is kept up by or on behalf of the mortgagor to the amount in which`
  line `the mortgagee is hereby authorised to insure.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 37, ibid., for certain words.`
  line
  line `2. Clause (a) omitted by s. 37, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 37, ibid., for "its preservation".`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 37.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 37, ibid., for certain words.`
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (44178)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 81
  title `Right to proceeds of revenue sale or compensation on acquisition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 38, ibid., for section 78.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44178&sectionno=73&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `^1[73. Right to proceeds of revenue sale or compensation on acquisition.-- (1) Where the`
  line `mortgaged property or any part thereof or any interest therein is sold owing to failure to pay`
  line `arrears of revenue or other charges of a public nature or rent due in respect of such property,`
  line `and such failure did not arise from any default of the mortgage e, the mortgagee shall be`
  line `entitled to claim payment of the mortgage-money, in whole or in part, out of any surplus of`
  line `the sale-proceeds remaining after payment of the arrears and of all charges and deductions`
  line `directed by law.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the mortgaged property or any part thereof or any interest therein is acquired`
  line `under the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), or any other enactment for the time being`
  line `in force providing for the compulsory acquisition of immoveable property, the mortgagee`
  line `shall be entitled to claim payment of the mortgage-money, in whole or in part, out of the`
  line `amount due to the mortgagor as compensation.`
  line
  line `(3) Such claims shall prevail against all other claims except those of prior encumbrances, and`
  line `may be enforced notwithstanding that the principal money on the mortgage has not become due.]`
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (44179)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 82
  title [Repealed.].
