obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (44181)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 84
  title `Liabilities of mortgagee in possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44181&sectionno=76&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `When, during the continuance of the mortgage, the`
  line `mortgagee takes possession of the mortgaged property,--`
  line
  line `(a) he must manage the property as a person of ordinary prudence would manage it if it were his`
  line own;
  line
  line `(b) he must use his best endeavours to collect the rents and profits thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) he must, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, out of the income of the property,`
  line `pay the Government-revenue, all other charges of a public nature ^1[and all rent] accruing due in`
  line `respect thereof during such possession, and any arrears of rent in default of payment of which`
  line `theproperty may be summarily sold;`
  line
  line `(d) he must, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, make such necessary repairs of the`
  line `property as he can pay for out of the rents and profits thereof after deducting from such rents and`
  line `profits the payments mentioned in clause (c) and the interest on the principal money;`
  line
  line `(e) he must not commit any act which is destructive or permanently injurious to the property;`
  line
  line `(f) where he has insured the whole or any part of the property against loss or damage by fire,`
  line `he must, in case of such loss or damage, apply any money which he actually receives under the policy, or. so much thereof as may be necessary, in reinstating the property, or, if the mortgagor so`
  line `directs, in reduction or discharge of the mortgage-money;`
  line
  line `(g) he must keep clear, full and accurate accounts of all sums received and spent by him as`
  line `mortgagee, and, at any time during the continuance of the mortgage, give the mortgagor, at his`
  line `request and cost, true copies of such accounts and of the vouchers by which they are`
  line supported;
  line
  line `(h) his receipts from the mortgaged property, or, where such property is personally occupied`
  line `by him. a fair occupation-rent in respect thereof shall, after deducting the expenses ^2[properly`
  line `incurred for the management of the property and the collection of rents and profits and the other`
  line `expenses] mentioned in clauses (c) and (d), and interest thereon, be debited against him in`
  line `reduction of the amount (if any) from time to time due to him on account of interest ^3*** and, so`
  line `far as such receipts exceed any interest due, in reduction or discharge of the mortgage-money; the`
  line `surplus, if any, shall be paid to the mortgagor;`
  line
  line `(i) when the mortgagor tenders, or deposits in manner hereinafter provided, the amount for the`
  line `time being due on the mortgage, the mortgagee must, notwithstanding the provisions in the other`
  line `clauses .of this section, account for his ^4*** receipts from the mortgaged property from the date of`
  line `the tender or from the earliest time when he could take such amount out of Court, as the case may be`
  line `'and shall not be entitled to deduct any amount therefrom on account of any expenses incurred after`
  line `such date or time in connection with the mortgaged property.`
  line
  line `Loss occasioned by his default.-- If the mortgagee fail to perform any of the duties imposed`
  line `upon him by this section, he may, when accounts are taken in pursuance of a decree made`
  line `under this Chapter, be debited with the loss, if any, occasioned by such failure.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 40, ibid.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 40.`
  line
  line `3. The words "on the mortgage-money" omitted by s. 40, ibid.`
  line
  line `4. The word "gross" omitted by s. 40, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (44182)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 85
  title `Receipts in lieu of interests.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44182&sectionno=77&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in section 76, clauses (b), (d), (g) and (h), applies`
  line `to cases where there is a contract between the mortgagee and the mortgagor that the receipts`
  line `from the mortgaged property shall, so long as the mortgagee is in possession of the property, be`
  line `taken in lieu of interest on the principal money, or in lieu of such interest and defined portions of`
  line `the principal.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (44183)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 86
  title `Postponement of prior mortgagee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44183&sectionno=78&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Where, through the fraud, misrepresentation or`
  line `gross neglect of a prior mortgagee, another person has been induced to advance money on the`
  line `security of the mortgaged property, the prior mortgagee shall be postponed to the subsequent`
  line mortgagee.
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (44184)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 87
  title `Mortgage to secure uncertain amount when maximum is expressed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44184&sectionno=79&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `If a mortgage`
  line `made to secure future advances, the performance of an engagement or the balance of a running`
  line `account, expresses the maximum to be secured thereby, a subsequent mortgage of the same`
  line `property shall, if made with notice of the prior mortgage, be postponed to the prior mortgage`
  line `in respect of all advances or debits not exceeding the maximum, though made or allowed with`
  line `notice of the subsequent mortgage.`
  line
  line Illustration
  line
  line `A mortgages Sultanpur to his bankers, B & Co., to secure the balance of his account with them to the extent`
  line `of Rs. 10,000. A then mortgages Sultanpur to C, to secure Rs. 10,000; C having not ice of the mortgage to B &`
  line `Co., and C gives notice to B & Co. of the second mortgage. At the date of the second mortgage, the balance due to`
  line `B & Co. does not exceed Rs. 5,000. B & Co. subsequently advance to A sums making the balance of the account`
  line `against him exceed the sum of Rs. 10,000. B & Co. are entitled to the extent of Rs. 10,000, to priority over C.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
