obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (44186)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 89
  title `Marshalling securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 42, for s. 81.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44186&sectionno=81&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `^1[81. Marshalling securities.-- If the owner of two or more properties mortgages them to`
  line `one person and then mortgages one or more of the properties to another person, the subsequent`
  line `mortgagee is, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, entitled to have the prior mortgagedebt satisfied out of the property or properties not mortgaged to him, so far as the same will`
  line `extend, but not so as to prejudice the rights of the prior mortgagee or of any other person who`
  line `has for consideration acquired an interest in any of the properties.]`
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (44187)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 90
  title `Contribution to mortgage-debt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44187&sectionno=82&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `^1[Where property subject to a mortgage belongs to`
  line `two or more persons having distinct and separate rights of ownership therein, the different`
  line `shares in or parts of such property owned by such persons are, in the absence of a contract to`
  line `the contrary, liable to contribute rateably to the debt secured by the mortgage, and, for the`
  line `purpose of determining the rate at which each such share or part shall contribute, the value`
  line `thereof shall be deemed to be its value at the date of the mortgage after deduction of the`
  line `amount of any other mortgage or charge to which it may have been subject on that date.]`
  line
  line `Where, of two properties belonging to the same owner, one is mortgaged to secure one`
  line `debt and then both are mortgaged to secure another debt, and the former debt is paid out of`
  line `the former property, each property is, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, liable to`
  line `contribute rateably to the latter debt after deducting the amount of the former debt fr om the`
  line `value of the property out of which it has been paid.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section applies to a property liable under section 81 to the claim of the ^2[subsequent]`
  line mortgagee.
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs by s. 43, ibid., for the first paragraph.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 43, ibid., for "second".`
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (44188)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 91
  title `Power to deposit in Court money due on mortgage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44188&sectionno=83&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `At any time after the principal`
  line `money ^1[payable in respect of any mortgage has become due] and before a suit for redemption`
  line `of the mortgaged property is barred, the mortgagor, or any other person entitled to institute such`
  line `suit, may deposit, in any Court in which he might have instituted such suit, to the account of the`
  line `mortgagee, the amount remaining due on the mortgage.`
  line
  line `Right to money deposited by mortgagor.-- The Court shall thereupon cause written notice`
  line `of the deposit to be served on the mortgagee, and the mortgage e may, on presenting a petition`
  line `(verified in manner prescribed by ^2law for the verification of plaints) stating the amount then`
  line `due on the mortgage, and his willingness to accept the money so deposited in full discharge of`
  line `such amount, and-on depositing in the same Court the mortgage-deed ^3[and all documents in`
  line `his possession or power relating to the mortgaged property], apply for and receive the money,`
  line `and the mortgage-deed, ^4[and all such other documents], so deposited hail be delivered to the`
  line `mortgagor or such other person as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `^4[Where the mortgagee is in possession of the mortgaged. property, the Court shall, before`
  line `paying to him the amount so deposited direct him to deliver possession thereof to the mortgagor`
  line `and at the cost of the mortgagor either to re-transfer the mortgaged property to the mortgagor or`
  line `to such third person as the mortgagor may direct or to execute and (where the mortgage has`
  line `been effected by a registered instrument) have registered an acknowledgment in writing that any`
  line `right in derogation of the mortgagor's interest transferred to the mortgagee has been`
  line extinguished.]
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 44, ibid., for "has become payable".`
  line
  line `2. See the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), Sch. I, Order VI, rule 15.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 44, for "if then in his possession or power ".`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 44, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (44189)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 92
  title `Cessation of interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44189&sectionno=84&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `When the mortgagor or such other person as aforesaid has`
  line `tendered or deposited in Court under section 83 the amount remaining due on the mortgage, interest on the principal money shall cease from the date of the tender or ^1[in the case of a`
  line `deposit, where no previous tender of such amount has been made], as soon as the mortgagor or`
  line `such other person as aforesaid has done all that has to be done by him to enable the mortgagee`
  line `to take such amount out of Court, ^2[and the notice required by section 83 has been served on`
  line `the mortgagee:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the mortgagor has deposited such amount without having made a`
  line `previous tender thereof and has subsequently withdrawn the same or any part thereof, interest`
  line `on the principal money shall be payable from the date of such withdrawal].`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section or in section 83 shall be deemed to deprive the mortgagee of his`
  line `right to interest when there exists a contract that he shall be entitled to reasonable notice`
  line `before payment or tender of the mortgage-money ^3[and such notice has not been given before`
  line `the making of the tender or deposit, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 45.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 45, ibid., for "as the case may be".`
  line
  line `3. Added by s. 45, ibid.`
