obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (44196)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 99
  title `Persons who may sue for redemption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 46, for section 91.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44196&sectionno=91&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `^1[91. Persons who may sue for redemption.-- Besides the mortgagor, any of the following persons`
  line `may redeem, or institute a suit for redemption of, the mortgaged property, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) any person (other than the mortgagee of the interest sought to be redeemed) who has any`
  line `interest in, or charge upon, the property mortgaged or in or upon the right to redeem the same;`
  line
  line `(b) any surety for the payment of the mortgage -debt or any part thereof; or`
  line
  line `(c) any creditor of the mortgagor who has in a suit for the administration of his estate obtained a`
  line `decree for sale of the mortgaged property.]`
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (44197)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 100
  title Subrogation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 47, ibid. Original ss. 92 to 94 were rep. by Act 5 of 1908, s. 156 and the fifth Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44197&sectionno=92&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `^1[92. Subrogation.-- Any of the persons referred to in section 91 (other than the mortgagor) and`
  line `any co-mortgagor shall, on redeeming property subject to the mortgage, have, so far as regards`
  line `redemption, foreclosure or sale of such property, the same rights as the mortgagee whose mortgage he`
  line `redeems may have against the mortgagor or any other mortgagee.`
  line
  line `The right conferred by this section is called the right of subrogation, and a person acquiring the same`
  line `is said to be subrogated to the rights of the mortgagee whose mortgage he redeems.`
  line
  line `A person who has advanced to a mortgagor money with which the mortgage has been redeemed`
  line `shall be subrogated to the rights of the mortgagee whose mortgage has been redeemed, if the`
  line `mortgagor has by a registered instrument agreed that such persons shall be so subrogated.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section shall be deemed to confer a right of subrogation on any person unless`
  line `the mortgage in respect of which the right is claimed has been redeemed in full.]`
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (44198)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 101
  title `Prohibition of tacking.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 47, ibid. Original ss. 92 to 94 were rep. by Act 5 of 1908, s. 156 and the fifth Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44198&sectionno=93&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `^1[93. Prohibition of tacking-- No mortgagee paying off a prior mortgage, whether with or`
  line `without notice of an intermediate mortgage, shall thereby acquire any priority in respect of his`
  line `original security; and, except in the case provided for by section 79, no mortgagee- making a`
  line `subsequent advance to the mortgagor, whether with or without notice of an intermediate mortgage, shall thereby acquire any priority in respect of his security for such subsequent advance.]`
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (44199)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 102
  title `Right of mesne mortgagee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 47, ibid. Original ss. 92 to 94 were rep. by Act 5 of 1908, s. 156 and the fifth Schedule.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44199&sectionno=94&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `^1[94. Rights of mesne mortgagee.-- Where a property is mortgaged for successive debts to successive`
  line `mortgagees, a mesne mortgagee has the same rights against mortgagees posterior to himself as he has`
  line `against the mortgagor.]`
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (44200)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 103
  title `Right of redeeming co-mortgagor to expenses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 48, for section 95. Original s. 96 was rep. by Act 5 of 1908, s. 156 and Sch. V.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44200&sectionno=95&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `^1[95. Right of redeeming co-mortgagor to expenses.-- Where one of several mortgagors`
  line `redeems the mortgaged property, he shall, in enforcing his right of subrogation under section 92`
  line `against his co-mortgagors, be entitled to add to the mortgage-money recoverable from them such`
  line `proportion of the expenses properly incurred in such redemption as is attributable to their share in the`
  line property.]
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (44201)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 104
  title `Mortgage by deposit of title-deeds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 48, for section 95. Original s. 96 was rep. by Act 5 of 1908, s. 156 and Sch. V.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44201&sectionno=96&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `^1[96. Mortgage by deposit of title-deeds-- The provisions hereinbefore contained which apply to a`
  line `simple mortgage shall, so far as may be, apply to a mortgage by deposit of title-deeds.]`
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (44202)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 105
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes `1. For the repealed provisions, as re-enacted, see (Act 5 of 1908), Sch. I, Order XXXIV, rules 12 and 13.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44202&sectionno=97&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `^1[Application of proceeds.] Rep. by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), s. 156 and the`
  line `Fifth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (44203)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 106
  title `Rights and liabilities of parties to anomalous mortgages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 49, for certain words.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44203&sectionno=98&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `In the case of ^1[an anomalous`
  line `mortgage] the rights and liabilities of the parties shall be determined by their contract as evidenced`
  line `in the mortgage-deed, and, so far as such contract does not extend, by local usage.`
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (44204)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 107
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes `1. For the repealed provisions, as re-enacted, see (Act 5 of 1908), Sch. I, Order XXXIV, rule 14.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44204&sectionno=99&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `^1[Attachment of mortgaged property.] Rep. by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908),`
  line `s. 156 and the Fifth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (44205)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 108
  title Charges.
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44205&sectionno=100&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `Where immoveable property of one person is by act of parties or operation of law`
  line `made security for the payment of money to another, and the transaction does not amount to a mortgage,`
  line `the latter person is said to have a charge on the property; and all the provisions hereinbefore contained`
  line `^1[which apply to a simple mortgage shall, so far as may be, apply to such charge].`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section applies to the charge of a trustee on the trust property for expenses`
  line `properly incurred in the execution of his trust, ^2[and, save as otherwise expressly provided by any`
  line `law for the time being in force, no charge shall be enforced against any property in the hands of a`
  line `person to whom such property has been transferred for consideration and without notice of the`
  line charge.]
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s 50, for certain words.`
  line
  line `2. Added by s. 50, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (44206)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 109
  title `No merger in case of subsequent encumbrance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 51, ibid., for section 101.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44206&sectionno=101&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `^1[101. No merger in case of subsequent encumbrance.-- Any mortgagee of, or person having`
  line `a charge upon, immoveable property, or any transferee from such Mortgagee or charge-holder, may`
  line `purchase or otherwise acquire the rights in the property of the mortgagor or owner, as the case may`
  line `be, without thereby causing the mortgage or charge to be merged as between himself and any`
  line `subsequent mortgagee of, or person having a subsequent charge upon, the same property; and no`
  line `such subsequent mortgagee or charge-holder shall be entitled to for close or sell such property`
  line `without redeeming the prior mortgage or charge, or otherwise than subject thereto.]`
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (44207)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 110
  title `Service or tender on or to agent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44207&sectionno=102&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `Where the person on or to whom any notice or tender`
  line `is to be served or made under this Chapter does not reside in the district in which the mortgaged`
  line `property or some part thereof is situate, service or tender on or to an agent holding a general`
  line `power-of-attorney from such person or otherwise duly authorised to accept such service or tender`
  line `shall be deemed sufficient.`
  line
  line `^1[Where no person or agent on whom such notice should be served can be found or is known] to`
  line `the person required to serve the notice, the latter person may apply to any Court in which a suit`
  line `might be brought for redemption of the mortgaged property, and such Court shall direct in what`
  line `manner such notice shall be served, and any notice served in compliance with such direction shall`
  line `be deemed Sufficient:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that, in the case of a notice required by section 83, in the case of a deposit, the application`
  line `shall be made to the Court in which the deposit has been made.]`
  line
  line `^3[Where no person or agent to whom such tender should be made can be found or is`
  line `known] to the person desiring to make the tender, the latter person may deposit, ^4[in any Court in which`
  line `a suit might be brought for redemption of the mortgaged property] the amount sought to be tendered, and`
  line `such deposit shall have the effect of a tender of such amount.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 52, for certain words.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 52, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 52, for certain words.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 52, ibid., for "in such Court as last aforesaid".`
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (44208)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 111
  title `Notice, etc., to or by person incompetent to contract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44208&sectionno=103&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `Where, under the provisions of`
  line `this Chapter, a notice is to be served on or by, or a tender or deposit made or accepted or taken out`
  line `of Court by, any person incompetent to contract, such notice may be served ^1[on or by], or tender or`
  line `deposit made, accepted or taken, by the legal curator of the property of such person; but where there`
  line `is no such curator, and it is requisite or desirable in the interests of such person that a notice should`
  line `be served or a tender or deposit made under the provisions of this Chapter, application may be made`
  line `to any Court in which a suit might be brought for the redemption of the mortgage to appoint a`
  line `guardian ad litem for the purpose of serving or receiving service of such notice, or making or`
  line `accepting such tender, or making or taking out of Court such deposit, and for the performance of all`
  line `consequential acts which could or ought to be done by such person if he were competent to contract;`
  line `and the provisions of ^2[Order XXXII in the First Schedule to the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908)] shall, so far as may be, apply to such application and to the parties thereto and to the`
  line `guardian appointed thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 53, ibid.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 53, ibid., for "Chapter XXXI of the Code of Civil Procedure".`
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (44209)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 112
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44209&sectionno=104&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may, from time to time, make rules consistent`
  line `with this Act for carrying out, in itself and in the Courts of Civil Judicature subject to its`
  line `superintendence, the provisions contained in this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (44210)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 113
  title `Lease defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44210&sectionno=105&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `A lease of immoveable property is a transfer of a right to enjoy such property,`
  line `made for a certain time, express or implied, or in perpetuity, in consideration of a price paid or promised,`
  line `or of money, a share of crops, service or any other thing of value, to be rendered periodically or on`
  line `specified occasions to the transferor by the transferee, who accepts the transfer on such terms.`
  line
  line `Lessor, lessee, premium and rent defined.-- The transferor is called the lessor, the transferee is called`
  line `the lessee, the price is called the premium, and the money, share, service or other thing to be so rendered`
  line `is called the rent.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (44211)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 114
  title `Duration of certain leases in absence of written contract or local usage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2003, s. 2, for section 106 (w.e.f. 31-12-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44211&sectionno=106&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `^1[106. Duration of certain leases in absence of written contract or local usage.-- (1) In the`
  line `absence of a contract or local law or usage to the contrary, a lease of immovable property for agricultural`
  line `or manufacturing purposes shall be deemed to be a lease from year to year, terminable, on the part of`
  line `either lessor or lessee, by six months' notice; and a lease of immovable property for any other purpose`
  line `shall be deemed to be a lease from month to month, terminable, on the part of either lessor or lessee, by`
  line `fifteen days' notice.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the period`
  line `mentioned in sub-section (1) shall commence from the date of receipt of notice.`
  line
  line `(3) A notice under sub-section (1) shall not be deemed to be invalid merely because the period`
  line `mentioned therein falls short of the period specified under that sub-section, where a suit or proceeding is`
  line `filed after the expiry of the period mentioned in that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) Every notice under sub-section (1) must be in writing, signed by or on behalf of the person giving`
  line `it, and either be sent by post to the party who is intended to be bound by it or be tendered or delivered`
  line `personally to such party, or to one of his family or servants at his residence, or (if such tender or delivery`
  line `is not practicable) affixed to a conspicuous part of the property.]`
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (44212)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 115
  title `leases how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44212&sectionno=107&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `A lease of immoveable property from year to year, or for any term`
  line `exceeding one year, or reserving a yearly rent, can be made only by a registered instrument.`
  line
  line `^1[All other leases of immoveable property may be made either by a registered instrument or by oral`
  line `agreement accompanied by delivery of possession.`
  line
  line `^2[Where a lease of immoveable property is made by a registered instrument, such`
  line `instrument or, where there are more instruments than one, each such instrument shall be`
  line `executed by both the lessor and the lessee:]`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, ^3 *** from time to time, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, direct that leases of immoveable property, other than leases from year to year,`
  line `or for any term exceeding one year, or reserving a yearly rent, or any class of such leases, may`
  line `be made by unregistered instrument or by oral agreement without delivery of possession.]`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1904, s. 5, for the Second paragraph.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 55.`
  line
  line `3. The words "with the previous sanction of the Governor General in Council" omitted by the A. O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (44213)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 116
  title `Rights and liabilities of lessor and lessee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44213&sectionno=108&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `In the absence of a contract or local`
  line `usage to the contrary, the lessor and the lessee of immoveable property, as against one another,`
  line `respectively, possess the rights and are subject to the liabilities mentioned in the rules next`
  line `following, or such of them as are applicable to the property leased:--`
  line
  line `(A) Rights and liabilities of the lessor`
  line
  line `(a) the lessor is bound to disclose to the lessee any material defect in the property, with reference`
  line `to its intended use, of which the former is and the latter is not aware, and which the latter could not`
  line `with ordinary care discover:`
  line
  line `(b) the lessor is bound on the lessee's request to put him in possession of the property:`
  line
  line `(c) the lessor shall be deemed to contract with the lessee that, if the latter pays the rent`
  line `reserved by the lease and performs the contracts binding on the lessee, he may hold the`
  line `property during the time limited by the lease without interruption.`
  line
  line `The benefit of such contract shall be annexed to and go with the lessee's interest as such, and may`
  line `be enforced by every person in whom that interest is for the whole or any part thereof from time to`
  line `time vested;`
  line
  line `(B) Rights and liabilities of the lessee`
  line
  line `(d) if during the continuance of the lease any accession is made to the property, such accession`
  line `(subject to the law relating to alluvion for the time being in force) shall be deemed to be comprised in`
  line `the lease:`
  line
  line `(e) if by fire, tempest or flood, or violence of an army or of a mob, or other irresistible`
  line `force, any material part of the property be wholly destroyed or rendered substantially and permanently unfit for the purposes for which it was let, the lease shall, at the option of the`
  line `lessee, be void:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the injury be occasioned by the wrongful act or default of the lessee,`
  line `he shall not be entitled to avail himself of the benefit of this provision:`
  line
  line `(f) if the lessor neglects to make, within a reasonable time after notice, any repairs which`
  line `he is bound to make to the property, the lessee may make the same himself, and deduct the`
  line `expense of such repairs with interest from the rent, or otherwise recover it from the lessor:`
  line
  line `(g) if the lessor neglects to make any payment which he is bound to make, and which if not`
  line `made by him, is recoverable from the lessee or against the property, the lessee may make such`
  line `payment himself, and deduct it with interest from the rent, or otherwise recover it from the`
  line `lessor:`
  line
  line `(h) the lessee may ^1[even after the determination of the lease] remove, at any time ^2[`
  line `whilst he is`
  line `in possession of the property leased but not afterwards,] all things which he has attached to the earth:`
  line
  line `provided he leaves the property in the state in which he received it:`
  line
  line `(i) when a lease of uncertain duration determines by any means except the fault of the lessee, he`
  line `or his legal representative is entitled to all the crops planted or sown by the lessee and growing upon`
  line `the property when the lease determines, and to free ingress and egress to gather and carry them:`
  line
  line `(j) the lessee may transfer absolutely or by way of mortgage or sub-lease the whole or any part of`
  line `his interest in the property, and any transferee of such interest or part may again transfer it. The lessee`
  line `shall not, by reason only of such transfer, cease to be subject to any of the liabilities attaching to the`
  line `lease:`
  line
  line `nothing in this clause shall be deemed to authorise a tenant having an untransferable right of`
  line `occupancy, the farmer of an estate in respect of which default has been made in paying revenue, or`
  line `the lessee of an estate under the management of a Court of Wards, to assign his interest as such`
  line `tenant, farmer or lessee:`
  line
  line `(k) the lessee is bound to disclose to the lessor any fact as to the nature or extent of the interest`
  line `which the lessee is about to take, of which the lessee is, and the lessor is not, aware, and which`
  line `materially increases the value of such interest:`
  line
  line `(l) the lessee is bound to pay or tender, at the proper time and place, the premium or rent to the`
  line `lessor or his agent in this behalf:`
  line
  line `(m) the lessee is bound to keep, and on the termination of the lease to restore, the property`
  line `in as good condition as it was in at the time when he was put in possession, subject only to the`
  line `changes caused by reasonable wear and tear or irresistible force, and to allow the lessor and his`
  line `agents, at all reasonable times during the term, to enter upon the property and inspect the`
  line `condition thereof and give or leave notice of any defect in such condition; and, when such`
  line `defect has been caused by any act or default on the part of the lessee, his servants or agents, he`
  line `is bound to make it good within three months after such notice has been given or left:`
  line
  line `(n) if the lessee becomes aware of any proceeding to recover the property or any part`
  line `thereof, or of any encroachment made upon, or any interference with, the lessor's rights`
  line `concerning such property, he is bound to give, with reasonable diligence, notic e thereof to the`
  line `lessor:`
  line
  line `(o) the lessee may use the property and its products (if any) as a person of ordinary prudence`
  line `would use them if they were his own; but he must not use, or permit another to use, the property`
  line `for a purpose other than that for which it was leased, or fell ^1[or sell] timber, pull down or`
  line `damage buildings ^1[belonging to the lessor or] work mines or quarries not open when the lease`
  line `was granted, or commit any other act which is destructive or permanently injurious thereto:`
  line
  line `(p) he must not, without the lessor's consent, cerrect on the property any permanent structure,`
  line `except for agricultural purposes:`
  line
  line `(q) on the determination of the lease, the lessee is bound to put the lessor into possession of the`
  line property.
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 56.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 56, ibid., for "during the continuance of the lease".`
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (44214)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 117
  title `Rights of lessor‟s transferee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44214&sectionno=109&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `If the lessor transfers the property leased, or any part thereof, or`
  line `any part of his interest therein, the transferee, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, shall possess all`
  line `the rights and, if the lessee so elects, be subject to all the liabilities of the lessor as to the property or part`
  line `transferred so long as he is the owner of it; but the lessor shall not, by reason only of such transfer, cease`
  line `to be subject to any of the liabilities imposed upon him by the lease, unless the lessee elects to treat the`
  line `transferee as the person liable to him:`
  line
  line `Provided that the transferee is not entitled to arrears of rent due before the transfer, and that,`
  line `if the lessee, not having reason to believe that such transfer has been made, pays rent to the`
  line `lessor, the lessee shall not be liable to pay such rent over again to the transferee.`
  line
  line `The lessor, the transferee and the lessee may determine what proportion of the premium or`
  line `rent reserved by the lease is payable in respect of the part so transferred, and, in case they`
  line `disagree, such determination may be made by any Court having jurisdiction to entertain a suit for`
  line `the possession of the property leased.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (44215)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 118
  title `Exclusion of day on which term commences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44215&sectionno=110&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `Where the time limited by a lease of`
  line `immoveable property is expressed as commencing from a particular day, in computing that time such`
  line `day shall be excluded. Where no day of commencement is named, the time so limited begins from the`
  line `making of the lease.`
  line
  line `Duration of lease for a year.-- Where the time so limited is a year or a number of years, in`
  line `the absence of an express agreement to the contrary, the lease shall last during the whole`
  line `anniversary of the day from which such time commences.`
  line
  line `Option to determine lease.-- Where the time so limited is expressed to be terminable before its`
  line `expiration, and the lease omits to mention at whose option it is so terminable, the lessee, and not the`
  line `lessor, shall have such option.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (44216)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 119
  title `Determination of lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44216&sectionno=111&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `A lease of immoveable property determines--`
  line
  line `(a) by efflux of the time limited thereby:`
  line
  line `(b) where such time is limited conditionally on the happening of some event--by the happening`
  line `of such event:`
  line
  line `(c) where the interest of the lessor in the property terminates on, or his power to dispose of`
  line `the same extends only to, the happening of any event--by the happening of such event:`
  line
  line `(d) in case the interests of the lessee and the lessor in the whole of the property become vested at`
  line `the same time in one person in the same right:`
  line
  line `(e) by express surrender; that is to say, in case the lessee yields up his interest under the lease to`
  line `the lessor, by mutual agreement between them:`
  line
  line `(f) by implied surrender:`
  line
  line `(g) by forfeiture; that is to say, (1) in case the lessee breaks an express condition which provides`
  line `that, on breach thereof, the lessor may re-enter ^1***; or (2) in case the lessee renounces his character`
  line `as such by setting up a title in a third person or by claiming title in himself; ^2[or (3) the lessee is`
  line `adjudicated an insolvent and the lease provides that the lessor may re-enter on the happening of such event]; and in ^3[any of these cases] the lessor or his transferee ^4[gives notice in writing to] the lessee`
  line `of his intention to determine the lease:`
  line
  line `(h) on the expiration of a notice to determine the lease, or to quit, or of intention to quit, the`
  line `property leased, duly given by one party to the other.`
  line
  line `Illustration to clause (f)`
  line
  line `A lessee accepts from his lessor a new lease of the property leased, to take effect during the`
  line `continuance of the existing lease. This is an implied surrender of the former lease, and such lease`
  line `determines thereupon.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or the lease shall become void" omitted by Act 20 of 1929, s. 57.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 57, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 57, for "either case".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 57, ibid., for "does some act showing".`
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (44217)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 120
  title `Waiver of forfeiture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44217&sectionno=112&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `A forfeiture under section 111, clause (g) is waived by`
  line `acceptance of rent which has become due since the forfeiture, or by distress for such rent, or by`
  line `any other act on the part of the lessor showing an intention to treat the lease as subsisting:`
  line
  line `Provided that the lessor is aware that the forfeiture has been incurred:`
  line
  line `Provided also that, where rent is accepted after the institution of a suit to eject the lessee on the`
  line `ground of forfeiture; such acceptance is not a waiver.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (44218)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 121
  title `Waiver of notice to quit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44218&sectionno=113&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `A notice given under section 111, clause (h), is waived, with the`
  line `express or implied consent of the person to whom it is given, by any act on the part of the person giving`
  line `it showing an intention to treat the lease as subsisting.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A, the lessor, gives B, the lessee, notice to quit the property leased. The notice expires, B tenders, and A`
  line `accepts, rent which has become due in respect of the property since the expiration of the notice. The notice is`
  line waived.
  line
  line `(b) A, the lessor, gives B, the lessee, notice to quit the property leased. The notice expires, and B`
  line `remains in possession. A gives to B as lessee a second notice to quit. The first notice is waived.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (44219)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 122
  title `Relief against forfeiture for non-payment of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44219&sectionno=114&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `Where a lease of immoveable`
  line `property has determined by forfeiture for non-payment of rent, and the lessor sues to eject the`
  line `lessee, if, at the hearing of the suit, the lessee pays or tenders to the lessor the rent in arrear,`
  line `together with interest thereon and his full costs of the suit, or gives such security as the Court`
  line `thinks sufficient for making such payment within fifteen days, the Court may, in lieu of making a`
  line `decree for ejectment, pass an order relieving the lessee against the forfeiture; and thereupon the`
  line `lessee shall hold the property leased as if the forfeiture had not occurred.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114_a:
  sectionId (44220)
  sectionNo 114A
  orderNo 123
  title `Relief against forfeiture in certain other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 58, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44220&sectionno=114A&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_114_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[114A. Relief against forfeiture in certain other cases.-- Where a lease of immoveable property`
  line `has determined by forfeiture for a breach of an express condition which provides that on breach thereof`
  line `the lessor may re-enter, no suit for ejectment shall lie unless and until the lessor has served on the lessee`
  line `a notice in writing--`
  line
  line `(a) specifying the particular breach complained of; and`
  line
  line `(b) if the breach is capable of remedy, requiring the lessee to remedy the breach;`
  line
  line `and the lessee fails, within a reasonable time from the date of the service of the notice, to remedy the`
  line `breach, if it is capable of remedy.`
  line
  line `Nothing in this section shall apply to an express condition against the assigning, underletting, parting with the possession, or disposing, of the property leased, or to an express`
  line `condition relating to forfeiture in case of non-payment of rent.]`
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (44221)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 124
  title `Effect of surrender and forfeiture on under-leases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44221&sectionno=115&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `The surrender, express or implied,`
  line `of a lease of immoveable property does not prejudice an under-lease of the property or any part`
  line `thereof previously granted by the lessee, on terms and conditions substantially the same (except as`
  line `regards the amount of rent) as those of the original lease; but, unless the surrender is made for the`
  line `purpose of obtaining a new lease, the rent payable by, and the contracts binding on, the under-lessee`
  line `shall be respectively payable to and enforceable by the lessor.`
  line
  line `The forfeiture of such a lease annuls all such under-leases, except where such forfeiture has been`
  line `procured by the lessor in fraud of the under-lessees, or relief against the forfeiture is granted under`
  line `section 114.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (44222)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 125
  title `Effect of holding over.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44222&sectionno=116&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `If a lessee or under-lessee of property remains in possession`
  line `thereof after the determination of the lease granted to the lessee, and the lessor or his legal`
  line `representative accepts rent from the lessee or under-lessee, or otherwise assents to his continuing in`
  line `possession, the lease is, in the absence of an agreement to the contrary, renewed from year to year, or`
  line `from month to month, according to the purpose for which the property is leased, as specified in section`
  line 106.
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A lets a house to B for five years. B underlets the house to C at a monthly rent of Rs. 100. The five years`
  line `expire, but C continues in possession of the house and pays the rent to A. C's lease is renewed from month to`
  line month.
  line
  line `(b) A lets a farm to B for the life of C. C dies, but B continues in possession with A's assent. B's lease is renewed from`
  line `year to year.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (44223)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 126
  title `Exemption of leases for agricultural purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44223&sectionno=117&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `None of the provisions of this`
  line `Chapter apply to leases for agricultural purposes, except in so far as the State Government`
  line `^1*** may by notification published in the Official Gazette, declare all or any of such`
  line `provisions to be so applicable ^2[in the case of all or any such leases], together with, or subject`
  line `to, those of the local law, if any, for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `Such notification shall not take effect until the expiry of six months from the date of its`
  line publication.
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "with the previous sanction of the Governor General in Council" omitted by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and`
  line `the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 6 of 1904, s. 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (44224)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 127
  title `“Exchange” defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44224&sectionno=118&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `When two persons mutually transfer the ownership of one`
  line `thing for the ownership of another neither thing or both things being money only, the`
  line `transaction is called an "exchange".`
  line
  line `A transfer of property in completion of an exchange can be made only in manner`
  line `provided for the transfer of such property by sale.]`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (44225)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 128
  title `Right of party deprived of thing received in exchange.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 59, for section 119.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44225&sectionno=119&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `^1[119. Right of party deprived of thing received in exchange-- If any party to an`
  line `exchange or any person claiming through or under such party is by reason of any defect in the`
  line `title of the other party deprived of the thing or any part of the thing received by him in`
  line `exchange, then, unless a contrary intention appears from the terms of the exchange, such other`
  line `party is liable to him or any person claiming through or under him for loss caused thereby, or`
  line `at the option of the person so deprived, for the return of the thing transferred, if still in the`
  line `possession of such other party or his legal representative or a transferee from h im without`
  line consideration.]
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (44226)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 129
  title `Rights and liabilities of parties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44226&sectionno=120&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Chapter,`
  line `each party has the rights and is subject to the liabilities of a seller as to that which he`
  line `gives, and the rights and is subject to the liabiliti es of a buyer as to that which he takes.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (44227)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 130
  title `Exchange of money.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44227&sectionno=121&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `On an exchange of money, each party thereby warrants`
  line `the genuineness of the money given by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (44228)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 131
  title `“Gift” defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44228&sectionno=122&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `Gift is the transfer of certain existing moveable or`
  line `immoveable property made voluntarily and without consideration, by one person, called`
  line `the donor, to another, called the donee, and accepted by or on behalf of the donee.`
  line
  line `Acceptance when to be made.-- Such acceptance must be made during the lifetime of`
  line `the donor and while he is till capable of giving,`
  line
  line `If the donee dies before acceptance, the gift is void.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (44229)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 132
  title `Transfer how effected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44229&sectionno=123&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of making a gift of immoveable`
  line `property, the transfer must be effected by a registered instrument signed by or on behalf of`
  line `the donor, and attested by at least two witnesses.`
  line
  line `For the purpose of making a gift of moveable property, the transfer may be effected`
  line `either by a registered instrument signed as aforesaid or by delivery.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (44230)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 133
  title `Gift of existing and future property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44230&sectionno=124&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `A girt comprising both existing and future`
  line `property is void as to the latter.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (44231)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 134
  title `Gift to several, of whom one does not accept.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44231&sectionno=125&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `A gift of a thing to two or more`
  line `donees, of whom one does not accept it, is void as to the interest which he would have`
  line `taken had he accepted.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (44232)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 135
  title `When gift may be suspended or revoked.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44232&sectionno=126&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `The donor and done may agree that`
  line `on the happening of any specified event which does not depend on the will of the donor a it`
  line `shall be suspended or revoked; but a gift which the parties agree shall be revocable wholly`
  line `or in part at the mere well of the donor is void wholly or in part, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `A gift also be revoked in any of the cases (save want or failure of consideration) in`
  line `which, if it were a contract, it might be rescinded.`
  line
  line `Save as aforesaid, a gift cannot be revoked.`
  line
  line `Nothing contained in this section shall be deemed to affect the rights of transferees for`
  line `consideration without notice.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) a gives a field to B, reserving to himself, with B's assent, the right to take back the field in case B`
  line `and his descendants dies before A, B dies without descendants in A's lifetime. A may take back the field.`
  line
  line `(b) A gives a lakh of rupees to B, reserving to himself, with B's assent, the right to take back at`
  line `pleasure Rs. 10, 000 out of the lakh. The gift holds good as to Rs. 90, 000, but is void as to Rs.10, 000,`
  line `which continue to belong to A.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (44233)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 136
  title `Onerous gifts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44233&sectionno=127&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `Where a gift is in the form of a single transfer to the same person`
  line `of several things of which one is, and the others are not, burdened by an obligation, the`
  line `done can take nothing by the gift unless he accepts it fully.`
  line
  line `Where a gift is in the form of two or more separate and independent transfers to the`
  line `same person of several things, the done is at liberty to accept one of them and refuse the`
  line `others, although the former may be beneficial and the latter onerous.`
  line
  line `Onerous gift to disqualified person.-- A done not competent to contract and accepting`
  line `property burdened by any obligation is not bound by his acceptance. But if, after becoming`
  line `competent to contract and being aware of the obligation, he retains the property given, he`
  line `becomes so bound.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A has shares in X, a prosperous joint stock company, and also shares in Y, a joint stock company, in`
  line `difficulties. Heavy calls are expected in respect of the shares in Y. A given B all his shares in joint stock`
  line `companies. B refuses to accept the shares in Y. He cannot take the shares in X.`
  line
  line `(b) A, having a lease for a term of years of a house at a rent which he and his representatives are bound`
  line `to pay during the term, and which is more than the house can be let for, given to B the lease, and also, as a`
  line `separate and independent transaction, a sum of money. B refuses to accept the lease. He does not by his`
  line `refusal forfeit the money.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (44234)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 137
  title `Universal donee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 60.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44234&sectionno=128&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 127, where a gift consists`
  line `of the donor's whole property, the done is personally liable for all the debts due by ^1[and`
  line `liabilities of] the donor at the time of the gift to the extent of the property comprised`
  line therein.
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (44235)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 138
  title `Saving of donations mortis causa and Muhammadan law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44235&sectionno=129&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `Nothing is this`
  line `Chapter related to gifts of moveable property made in contemplation of death, or shall be`
  line `deemed to affect any rule of Muhammadan law ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and figures "or, save as provided by section 123, any rule of Hindu or Buddhist law" omitted by Act 20 of`
  line `1929, s. 61.`
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (44236)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 139
  title `Transfer of actionable claim.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44236&sectionno=130&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `^1(1) The transfer of an actionable claim ^2[whether with`
  line `or without consideration] shall be effected only by the execution of an instrument in writing`
  line `signed by the transferor or his duly authorised agent, ^3*** shall be complete and effectual upon`
  line `the execution of such instrument, and thereupon all the rights and remedies of the transferor,`
  line `whether by way of damages or otherwise, shall vest in the transferee, whether such notice of the`
  line `transfer as is hereinafter provided be given or not:`
  line
  line `Provided that every dealing with the debt or other actionable claim by the debt or or other`
  line `person from or against whom the transferor would, but for such instrument of transfer as`
  line `aforesaid, have been entitled to recover or enforce such debt or other actionable claim, shall`
  line `(save where the debtor or other person is a party to the transfer or has received express notice`
  line `thereof as hereinafter provided) be valid as against such transfer.`
  line
  line `(2) The transferee of an actionable claim may, upon the execution of such instrument of`
  line `transfer as aforesaid, sue or institute proceedings for the same in his own name without`
  line `obtaining the transferor's consent to such suit or proceedings and without making him a party`
  line thereto.
  line
  line `Exception.-- Nothing in this section applies to the transfer of a marine or fire policy of`
  line `insurance ^4[or affects the provisions of section 38 of the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938).]`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(i) A owes money to B, who transfers the debt to C. B then demands the debt from A, who, not having`
  line `received notice of the transfer, as prescribed in section 131, pays B. The payment is valid, and C cannot sue A for`
  line `the debt.`
  line
  line `(ii) A effects a policy on his own life with an Insurance Company and assigns it to a Bank for securing the`
  line `payment of an existing or, future debt. If A dies, the Bank is entitled to receive the amount of the policy and to sue on`
  line `it without the concurrence of A's executor, subject to the proviso in sub-section (1) of section 130 and to the`
  line `provisions of section 132.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 1900, s. 4, for the original Chapter VIII.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 1929, s. 62.`
  line
  line `3. The words and figures "and notwithstanding anything contained in section 123" ins. by Act 38 of 1925, s. 2, omitted`
  line `by Act 20 of 1929, s. 62.`
  line
  line `4. Added by Act 4 of 1938, s. 121 (w.e.f. 1-7-1939).`
obj_root_law_sections_130_a:
  sectionId (44252)
  sectionNo 130A
  orderNo 140
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 6 of 1944, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44252&sectionno=130A&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_130_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[130A.Transfer of policy of marine insurance.] Rep. by the Marine Insurance Act, 1963`
  line `(11 of 1963), s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-8-1963).]`
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (44253)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 141
  title `Notice to be in writing, signed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44253&sectionno=131&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `Every notice of transfer of an actionable claim shall`
  line `be in writing, signed by the transferor or his agent duly authorised in this behalf, or, in case the transferor refuses to sign, by the transferee or his agent, and shall state the name and address of`
  line `the transferee.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (44238)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 142
  title `Liability of transferee of actionable claim.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44238&sectionno=132&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `The transferee of an actionable claim shall`
  line `take it subject to all the liabilities and equities to which the transferor was subject in respect`
  line `thereof at the date of the transfer.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(i) A transfers to C a debt due to him by B, A being then indebted to B. C sues B for the debt due by B to A.`
  line `such suit B is entitled to set off the debt due by A to him; although C was unaware of it at the date of such transfer.`
  line
  line `(ii) A executed a bond in favour of B under circumstances entitling the former to have it delivered up and`
  line `cancelled. B assigns the bond to C for value and without notice of such circumstances. C cannot enforce the bond`
  line `against A.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (44239)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 143
  title `Warranty of solvency of debtor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44239&sectionno=133&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `Where the transferor of a debt warrants the solvency of`
  line `the debtor, the warranty, in the absence of a contract to the contrary, applies only to his solvency at`
  line `the time of the transfer, and is limited, where the transfer is made for consideration, to the amount or`
  line `value of such consideration.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (44240)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 144
  title `Mortgaged debt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44240&sectionno=134&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `Where a debt is transferred for the purpose of securing an existing or`
  line `future debt, the debt so transferred, if received by the transferor or recovered by the transf eree, is`
  line `applicable, first, in payment of the costs of such recovery; secondly, in or towards satisfaction of the`
  line `amount for the time being secured by the transfer; and the residue, if any, belongs to the transferor`
  line `or other person entitled to receive the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (44241)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 145
  title `Assignment of rights under policy of insurance against fire.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1944, s. 3, for section 135.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44241&sectionno=135&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `^1[135. Assignment of rights under policy of insurance against fire.-- Every assignee by`
  line `endorsement or other writing, of a policy of insurance against fire, in whom the property in the subject`
  line `insured shall be absolutely vested at the date of the assignment, shall have transferred and vested in him`
  line `all rights of suit as if the contract contained in the policy had been made with himself.]`
obj_root_law_sections_135_a:
  sectionId (44242)
  sectionNo 135A
  orderNo 146
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44242&sectionno=135A&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_135_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[Assignment of rights under policy of marine insurance.] Rep. by the Marine Insurance Act,`
  line `1963 (11 of 1963), s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-8-1963).]`
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (44243)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 147
  title `Incapacity of officers connected with Courts of Justice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44243&sectionno=136&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `^1[136. Incapacity of officers connected with Courts of Justice.-- No Judge, legal practitioner, or`
  line `officer connected with any Court of Justice shall buy or traffic in, or stipulate for, or agree to receive, any`
  line `share of, or interest in, any actionable claim, and no Court of Justice shall enforce, at his instance, or at`
  line `the instance of any person claiming by or through him, any actionable claim so dealt with by him as`
  line aforesaid.]
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (44244)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 148
  title `Saving of negotiable instruments, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671&sectionId=44244&sectionno=137&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00042_188204_1523272233671
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `^1[137. Saving of negotiable instruments, etc.-- Nothing in the foregoing sections of this`
  line `Chapter applies to stocks, shares or debentures, or to instruments which are for the time being, by`
  line `law or custom, negotiable, or to any mercantile document of title to goods.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- The expression "mercantile document of title to goods" includes a bill of lading,`
  line `dock-warrant, warehouse-keeper's certificate, railway receipt, warrant or order for the delivery of`
  line `goods, and any other document used in the ordinary course of business as proof of the possession or`
  line `control of goods, or authorising or purporting to authorise, either by endorsement or by delivery, the`
  line `possessor of the document to transfer or receive goods thereby represented.]`
